title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop in hot fat by teaspoons.

title: bologna cake
directions: Blend cream cheese with Worcestershire, Tabasco and mustard. Start bottom layer of cake with bologna, then alternate with cheese spread.
Smooth remaining cheese mixture on top and sides like a regular cake.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Slice thinly and serve with a Ritz.

title: sausage balls
directions: Use hands to mix well.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces. Heat oil in skillet. Dredge chicken in salt, pepper and flour. Brown chicken, stirring often. Remove chicken from skillet. Add mushrooms, onions, pepper and chestnuts to skillet. Saute for 5 minutes. Dissolve bouillon in 1 1/4 cups boiling water and add soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and ginger. Add chicken back into skillet with vegetables. Stir in bouillon mixture. Cook over low heat until thick. Add cashews. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender.
Drain and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: In pot cook beef, sausage, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Prepare spaghetti.
Drain. Serve.

title: stuffed pumpkin
directions: Cut hole in top of pumpkin (save plug to use as a lid). Thoroughly scrape out contents of pumpkin.
Mix all of the rest of the ingredients and pack into pumpkin (fruit will shrink).
Replace top of pumpkin.
Place in baking dish or on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until fruit is tender.
Drizzle 1 to 2 tablespoons of wine or brandy.
Serve as a relish with meal.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients slowly.
Add zucchini, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour in a greased Bundt pan or until done.
Test with a toothpick.
If it comes out clean, bread is done.

title: marinade for pork or chicken
directions: Mix all together except meat.
Add meat and marinate at least 3 hours, turning frequently.

title: souper sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef in skillet until browned, pour off fat.
Add soup, water, worcestershire and pepper, heat through.
Serve on rolls. Serves 6.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: In a large kettle, brown sausage, beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cabbage.
Mix well.
Stir in cabbage and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: banana spice nut loaf
directions: Mash bananas, add oil and put aside.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream butter, sugar and add eggs one at a time.
Add banana mixture to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in loaf pans (any size) at 350°.
Cook until brown (test with toothpick).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli in microwave for 4 minutes.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and evaporated milk in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Place broccoli with water chestnuts.
Cover with milk mixture.
Spread cheeses over.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cover with dried French onions.
Bake another 8 to 10 minutes more.

title: potato casserole
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole, mix ingredients in order given.
Sprinkle top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jam crumpets
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Spread cut surface of each muffin half with 1 teaspoon each margarine and jam.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and coconut (or almonds).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 5 minutes or until bubbly and brown.
Yields 12 Crumpets.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box and drain.
Mix shredded cheese, mushroom soup, grated onion and mayonnaise together.
Add drained macaroni.
Bake in casserole dish in a 350° oven until cheese begins to bubble.
Remove and serve.

title: fatoosh
directions: Toast bread in 350° oven until crunchy and break into small pieces.
Place in large bowl.
Cut cucumbers and tomatoes in small chunks.
Mince parsley.
Put all of these vegetables over the bread.
Add mint, lemon juice, olive oil, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well; serve over romaine lettuce.

title: steak and mushroom gravy
directions: Trim steak and cut into small individual pieces. Preheat skillet with a small amount of butter and put in steak seasoned with garlic, salt and pepper. Brown meat on both sides and place in a baking dish. Warm soup in skillet and dump over meat. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies(easy and good!)
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and salt to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: clair torte
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, bring water, butter and salt to a boil.
Add flour at once. Stir until a smooth ball forms.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 mins.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well as you add them.
Spread into greased 13 X 9-inch pan and bake at 400° for 30 - 35 mins.
(It will be puffed golden brown). Cool completely.
Remove onto dish.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Spread over puff and refrigerate for 20 mins.
Spread on Cool Whip and drizzle Hershey's Chocolate Syrup over the top.

title: normandy-style duckling (france) caneton a la normandie
directions: Rinse duckling pieces; pat dry, cut away and discard excess fat.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet.
Sprinkle duckling pieces with salt and pepper.
Add duck to skillet.
Brown on all sides.
Pour off fat as it collects.
Quarter core, pare and sliced apples.
Melt remaining butter.
Saute apple slices.
Place thin layer of apple slices in buttered 3-quart casserole dish. Arrange duck over apples, plumes and pieces on top.
Surround with remaining apple.
Discard fat from skillet.
Add apple brandy to same skillet.
Stir over heat to loosen particles.
Heat until steaming.
Pour over duck; cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add other ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for an additional 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown onions.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add taco seasoning, mushroom soup and tomatoes.
Layer chips in a casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: easy frozen dessert
directions: Blend margarine and brown sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, coconut and chopped nuts.
Put 1/2 of mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ice cream over bottom layer; top with remaining mixture.
Freeze.

title: chicken strata
directions: Cut bread in 1-inch cubes and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine chicken, vegetables, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Spoon over bread cubes.
Sprinkle with remaining bread cubes.
Combine milk and eggs and pour over all.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Spoon soup over top and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top for last few minutes of baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix eggs, onion, mayo and soup.
Layer broccoli and cheese. Pour sauce over top.
Repeat.
Cover with prepared stuffing and butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Don't cover.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Warm the milk and dissolve the yeast along with water.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and let raise.
Roll out.
Put butter, sugar and cinnamon on rolled out dough, then roll up and cut.
Put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower, leaving it whole.
Drain well.
Place in shallow pan and frost with mayonnaise and mustard, mixed.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts. Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Very pretty holiday dish.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening together.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Press with a glass.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange sherbet gelatin salad
directions: Drain oranges.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water in pan, reheat if necessary.
Add sherbet when gelatin is partially cool. Fold in topping and oranges.
Sets up fast.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flavorings and buttermilk.
Mix together flour, soda and salt and add; mix well. Add German's chocolate that has been softened.
Blend together well.
Cook in 9-inch stem pan that has been well greased and dusted with flour, about 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Test with a toothpick.
If done, toothpick will come out clean when inserted in cake's center.
Place cake under tight fitting cake cover while still hot and leave covered until cold.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm (120°).
Add dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) pans that have been greased and sprinkle with cornmeal. Cover; let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.
To serve, slice and toast.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken and stove top stuffing
directions: Parboil and debone chicken breasts.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Place cooked, cut up chicken on bottom of baking dish.
Pour soup on top of chicken and then pour chicken broth over top.
Spread stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: watergate potatoes
directions: Preheat
oven
Slice potatoes and onions.
Put layer of potato, onion, potato, onion.
Wrap whole potato with slice of bacon.
Also
leave
skin
on potatoes.
Wrap each in aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put half in casserole.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Use 1/2 of chicken mixture over the dressing mixture, then add the rest of the dressing.
Beat 2 eggs slightly and add 1 1/2 cups milk and pour over top of casserole.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Pour 1 can mushroom soup over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, uncovered.
Add shredded cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
After mixing together, add oil and zucchini.
Sift together and add flour and soda, then stir in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour in casserole.
Cook at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: boy scout potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, mushroom soup, sour cream and onion all together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted butter and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown ground round in skillet and season with onion salt and Worcestershire sauce.
While browning, flatten each biscuit and align on cookie sheet.
Spread tomato sauce on each biscuit that has been flattened.
Drain meat and spoon a good bit onto each biscuit.
Top with cheese of your choice.
Bake in the oven, following directions on biscuit can or at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes. Allow to cool before eating.

title: crab mousse
directions: Coat a 4 cup mold with cooking spray.
In saucepan sprinkle gelatin over milk and let stand 1 minute.
Add cheese and cook over low heat until gelatin dissolves and is smooth.
Add yogurt and stir.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Unmold onto a plate and garnish with parsley.
Serve with buttery crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: the golden pheasant
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender.
For the drink, pour 1 ounce with Shasta creme soda to taste.
A family friend, Keith Clark from Omaha, Nebraska, introduced this refreshing beverage to us in 1976.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients, then mix all of these together.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Stir all together.
Pour in 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beans, beans and more beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or slow cooker 8 hours on slow. The longer you cook it, the better it is.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix meat, cracker crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk. Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonful into balls.
Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Brown and cook meat balls.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Pour excess fat from skillet.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns and place in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Melt one stick of butter, sour cream, chicken soup and cheese and pour over potatoes.
Crush corn flakes into melted butter and pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Spray pie plate with vegetable cooking spray.
Steam zucchini, broccoli, cauliflower florets, carrots, mushrooms, onions and green peppers in about 1/2 cup of water until tender.
Drain and place in pie plate.
Stir in cheese.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper; pour over vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: hearty beef chowder
directions: Combine ground beef, tomato juice, water and celery soup. Stir with large whisk to blend.
Stir in carrots, sugar, garlic salt, pepper and marjoram.
Bring mixture to boil over medium heat.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes.
To serve, place 1 slice Swiss cheese in bottom of bowl.
Pour hot soup over cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves six.

title: chill liver
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan, drain and crumble. Dust liver with flour.
Brown in bacon drippings.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Uncover and cook for a few additional minutes to thicken sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Beat eggs, cottage cheese and salt together.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pasulja iz kapusta(a russian specialty)
directions: Brown lamb with or without bone in stew style and drain off excess fat; with meat, brown onion and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 cup water and steam for 45 minutes.
Add 1 large can sauerkraut, which has been drained, 2 cans tomato sauce and a small head of cabbage, which has been finely cut.
To this, add a little more water and a grated small onion into it.
Cook 45 minutes, then add cans of kidney beans.

title: microwavable crispix mix
directions: Combine cereal, nuts and pretzels in a large glass bowl; set aside.
In a microwave-safe bowl, combine butter, garlic salt, onion salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Microwave on High until melted.
Pour over cereal mixture, stirring until coated.
Microwave on High 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes. Spread on paper towel to cool.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugars well.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour into crust; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in bowl the mashed bananas and beaten eggs.
Add flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and oleo.
Stir together and add nuts. Pour into oiled pan or muffin tins.
Bake 1 hour at 350° for loaf and 30 minutes for muffins.

title: long time cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery and sweet pepper.
Mix well the sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed; add to the cabbage mixture.
Can be made several days ahead.
Will keep a very long time in refrigerator.

title: velvet egg custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly pour into hot milk.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips.
Pour over cereal.
Put in paper bag.
Add powdered sugar and shake bag.

title: hot dogs made easy
directions: Place a hot dog inside a flour tortilla.
Add cheese, mustard and catsup.
Roll hot dog in tortilla and place in a paper towel. Microwave for 30 to 45 seconds.
Little ones can make this and love it.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch psatry lined pie pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: whipped cream biscuits
directions: In a bowl combine the flour and whipped cream. Turn dough onto a floured surface. Knead 10 times. Roll 3/4 inch in thickness. Cut with 2 1/4 in round cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: tomatoes and olive salsa
directions: Use tomatoes held at room temperature until fully ripe.
Core tomatoes; chop (makes about 2 cups).
Place in a medium bowl. Stir in olives, parsley, oil, oregano, garlic, vinegar and red pepper.
Serve at room temperature with bagel chips, toasted pita chips, tortilla chips or crisp bread.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: For Marinade:
In a large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, garlic, lime juice, oregano, cumin, salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 into another bowl.
Add chicken to one bowl and peppers and onion to another.
Cover and marinate in fridge at least 30 minutes.

title: technicolor rotini primavera
directions: In a large saute pan, put the mushrooms and the chicken stock on high
heat with a little salt and pepper.
When they're tender (about 5 minutes), add the onion and peppers and stir in the cabbage and cook for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon juice, milk and Cool Whip.
Add almond flavoring. Mix in other ingredients.

title: golden white-chunk nutty bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda and salt. In another medium bowl, with an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in the eggs, coconut and vanilla, then blend slowly until smooth.
Add the flour mixture, chopped chocolate and pecans.
Scrape the dough into the prepared baking pan; level and smooth the surface.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until the center is set and the top is golden.
Place the pan on a wire rack to cool to room temperature before cutting into 16 bars.
Yields 16 bars.

title: home style salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together 3/4 cup sugar and 1 1/2 tablespoons cinnamon. Set aside.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Beat until sugar is melted.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut breasts into about 6 nuggets, about 1 inch square. Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salts and herbs in plastic bag.
Dip chicken into melted butter, then into crumb mixture.
Place in single layer on foil pan or foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: company cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salt water until tender (about 8 minutes).
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Slowly add milk.
Add nutmeg, pepper and 3/4 cup cheese.
Drain cabbage well and combine with cheese mixture. Place in greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: artichoke dip *
directions: Drain artichokes and break into small pieces.
Mix with rest of ingredients and put into pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown on top. Serve warm with crackers.

title: tandoori style chicken
directions: Heat cumin, coriander, paprika and pepper in saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring until fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes (be careful not to burn).
Transfer to a large bowl and stir in yogurt, lemon juice, ginger, garlic, salt and food coloring. Remove skin from chicken, except wings and score flesh diagonally 1/2-inch deep.
Toss with yogurt mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: In a large
skillet, cook onion in hot oil until almost tender.
Add
meat	and
garlic; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered,
to
2	1/2 hours or until sauce is nice and thick.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Salt and pepper and add onion to taste. Place in casserole dish and pour frozen Tater Tots over meat. Mix the cream of celery soup and evaporated milk; pour over Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: bohemian crescents
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add flour.
Add pecans.
Put in refrigerator about 15 minutes.
By hand, shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop in greased muffin tins and cook 12 minutes at 450°.

title: creamy oyster broccoli stew
directions: Combine milk and soup in saucepan; stir in broccoli, potatoes and onion and cook over medium heat until bubbly (stirring occasionally); simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook oysters in saucepan until edges curl; add to broccoli mixture.

title: crabmeat sandwiches
directions: Put all in mixer; mix well.
Spread on bread, then cut into finger sandwiches.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour the milk into a large bowl.
Add the pudding mix and prepare in the bowl according to package directions. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in the whipped topping and half the crushed cookies. Place 1 tablespoon of remaining cookies into each 8 to 10 (7-ounce) plastic cups.
Fill cups about 3/4 full with the pudding mixture, then top with remaining cookies.
Chill 1 hour.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, cracker crumbs, egg and salt.
Shape into small balls.
Brown the meatballs in skillet; drain the grease when cooked.
Heat chili sauce and jelly until jelly has dissolved. Add meatballs to the sauce; continue cooking for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
You want to maintain a very low boil for this time period. May cook on top of stove or use an electric skillet.

title: banana split cake
directions: Put graham cracker crumbs in bottom of 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Mix together with mixer for 5 minutes the powdered sugar, eggs and oleo.
Pour on top of graham cracker crumbs.
Layer pineapple (drained), strawberries (cut up), bananas (cut up) and Cool Whip on top.
Chill and store in refrigerator.

title: red hot jelly
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan combine juice and sugar.
Stir well.
Add butter and red hots.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in pectin.
Return to rolling boil, stirring constantly for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Skim foam from top with metal spoon.
Fill sterilized jars to 1/4-inch thick.
Makes 4 1/2 pint jars.

title: egg bake
directions: Stir together; pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Make one day before.)
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and kraut
directions: In a 12-inch skillet in hot oil, brown chicken.
Remove chicken.
Add remaining ingredients to the skillet and mix well with the drippings.
Turn into an ungreased 13 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish and top with chicken, skin side up, in a single layer.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 325° until the chicken is tender, browned and the skin somewhat crisp, about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Serve with potatoes or dumplings, because the mixture is juicy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: country style corn bread for muffins, corn sticks or pone
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Spray muffin pans, corn stick molds or skillet with Pam.
Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix oil with buttermilk and add to dry mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour batter into greased pans (fill muffin cups and corn stick pans about 2/3 full; for corn pone, pour batter into greased skillet about 1-inch deep).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until as brown as desired on top.

title: strawberry meringue pie
directions: Place ingredients in double boiler and beat.
Place container over rapidly boiling water.
Beat steadily with wire whisk or rotary beater until the meringue will hold a peak (6 to 8 minutes).
Remove the container from heat and continue to beat for 3 minutes.
Fill the pie shell with 2 to 3 cups hulled strawberries or other tart fruit.
Cover with meringue.
Swirl on top for a professional effect.
Place pie under broiler to brown top lightly, if desired.
When cool, chill pie.

title: cookie mix
directions: Mix.
Put in 6 Ziploc bags; store in freezer.

title: taquitos
directions: Mix all together until spreadable.

title: party punch
directions: Mix only half amount of water called for on Kool-Aid directions.
Then proceed to add remaining liquids.
Stir until well blended.
Chill until ready to serve.
At serving time, add the sherbet and stir lightly.

title: savory crescent squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons melted margarine until smooth.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix well.

title: joe froggers
directions: Mix
1 cup sugar, shortening, molasses and water in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients except sugar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°; roll dough 1/4-inch thick on well floured surface.
Cut into 3-inch circles; sprinkle with sugar.
Place about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indention remains when touched, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.

title: sinfully rich sweet potatoes
directions: Beat all ingredients together and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.

title: lazy pirogi
directions: Mix butter, sauerkraut and onion and simmer for 1 hour.
Cook noodles for about 15 minutes.
Add to sauerkraut and mix together. Add another 1/2 lb. of butter while mixing.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Heat in warm oven. Serve with vegetables, chips or snack crackers.
I like to use grated peppers and onions instead of chopped.

title: sesame chicken strips
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the butter and soy sauce. In another bowl, combine the cracker crumbs, ginger and salt. Dip chicken strips in butter mixture, then roll in crumbs until coated on all sides. Place in a single layer on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Brown sausage; crumble and drain, reserving drippings.
Add margarine to drippings to measure 1/4 cup.
Set sausage and drippings aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in medium bowl.
Mix egg, milk and 1/4 cup drippings.
Stir well. Add liquid mixture to dry mixture and stir until moistened.
Stir in cheese and sausage.
Spoon into paper lined muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: war cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Place rest of ingredients in pan and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Add sifted ingredients to cooled mixture and blend well.
Bake 45 minutes in a greased loaf pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add food coloring, vanilla and eggs. Beat well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together more than once.
Put vinegar and soda in buttermilk.
Add flour and milk to creamed mixture, a little at a time.
Mix well. Pour batter into two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes. Watch carefully during the final phase of baking. Cool and ice.

title: chili sauce for hot dogs
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery in butter; add remaining ingredients and simmer one hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put ingredients in iron skillet and start heating.
Have oven hot and partial parch 2 cups peanuts (about 1/2 done).
Take out of oven and dump in skillet of mixture above.
Turn stove eye on high.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes until syrup is caramel light.
Set off stove and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Stir for a minute.
Pour in 2 greased cookie pans.
Smooth down.
When cold, break into pieces. Keep in tight covered container.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Combine beef, onion, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and seasonings and shape into small meatballs (size of a walnut). Bake on cookie sheet.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Brown ground beef and garlic in large skillet; drain.
Mix tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, oregano and pepper with ground beef.
Cover, simmer for 20 minutes. In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the following:
3 noodles, 1/3 meat mixture, 1/2 cottage cheese and 3 slices Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat the first 3 layers, then layer 3 noodles, 1/3 meat mixture and 3 slices cheese.
Then top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and oleo; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar and spread on cool crust.
Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Cool.
Stir into cool Jell-O 2 packages of frozen strawberries.
Put this mixture on top of cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Top with fresh strawberries.

title: wilted slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Mix. Place in covered jar and refrigerate.
Best if left to marinate for 24 to 48 hours.
Re-mix every 24 hours, you let it marinate.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: easy pie filling cake(tupperware cake; microwave only)
directions: *Examples:
Chocolate cake mix, cherry pie filling; lemon cake mix, peach pie filling.

title: apple pepper relish
directions: All ingredients are to be ground on an ole-timey sausage grinder very fine.
Cover with red vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Cook to turn peppers and brown about 10 minutes.
Makes about 15 to 16 pints canned.

title: basic buttercream frosting for cake decorating
directions: Mix flour and shortening together. Add other ingredients, a small amount at a time.

title: susan's chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients together making sauce.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Baste with 1/2 of the sauce.
Cover and cook at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add remaining sauce and cook uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes until browned.
May use drumettes.

title: chicken taos
directions: In frying pan, saute onions in butter until translucent.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Add chicken to onions and saute until pink color is gone.
Put all ingredients into pot and cook for about an hour.
When done, eat with rice and vegetables.

title: spicy baked beans
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Combine beans and cold water in 6 quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let soak 1 hour.

title: gumdrop fruitcake
directions: Reserve 2 cups flour to roll gumdrops, raisins and nuts in. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and applesauce.
Dissolve baking soda in 1 tablespoon hot water and add gumdrops, raisins and nuts.
Use 2 bread pans or 1 tube pan.
Bake at 300° to 350° for approximately 2 hours.

title: amaretto sours
directions: Use your lemonade can for all measurements.
Mix all together and freeze until slushy or overnight.
(If frozen, defrost for one hour; break into a slush.)

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cook yellow rice according to directions on bag.
Mix ground beef with Chili-O mix.
Layer ground beef and rice; top with Cheddar cheese soup.
Top with crushed corn chips.
Brown in 400° oven for 20 minutes, or until cheese bubbles.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Combine soup and cheese; heat over low heat until cheese is melted. Cook bacon and onions together. Drain on paper towels. Break bacon into small pieces. Add to soup mixture. Add half and half; simmer over low heat for 1/2 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine or butter with sugar. Mix in eggs and bananas until well blended.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips, cherries and nuts.
Divide batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: After browning and draining meat, add onion and simmer until transparent. Combine with remaining ingredients and place in a large casserole dish. Top with raw bacon strips and bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave sweet and sour sauce
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar, cornstarch and water until well blended.

Stir in pineapple, pepper, pimiento, garlic, vinegar, soy sauce and Tabasco and microwave 5 to 7 minutes on High, stirring every 2 minutes, until thick and clear. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to develop flavor.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together the Jello and Cool Whip, then add pineapple and oranges after draining off the juice. To this mixture add the cottage cheese and stir together mixing well. Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: mom's caramel pie
directions: Place 1 cup sugar in a frying pan and let melt until a brownish syrup forms. Add the 1/2 cup water to syrup and let boil until mixture is melted. Mix the other cup of sugar, flour, salt, milk, slightly beaten egg yolks and melted syrup in double boiler. Cook until mixture is thick. Add butter and vanilla and pour into cooked pie crust. Use egg whites for meringue. This makes a large pie.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: In large mixer bowl, stir flour, soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients, except candy, and beat at low speed of mixer until well combined, scraping bowl occasionally.
Chill dough 30 minutes.

title: hot apple punch
directions: Combine the apple juice and rum in a small punch bowl. To serve, ladle into cups. Top with a dollop of whipped cream and a sprinkling of cinnamon. Easy to double. Yield: 12 servings.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onion in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Do not stir.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together over hot water (double boiler). When melted, gently pour over cereal. Let cool some, then add sugar to coat. Let set, then add more sugar.

title: orange pineapple carrot jello salad
directions: Drain
crushed	pineapple
and reserve juice.
Dissolve Jell-O with
3 cups boiling water.
Add another cup liquid of pineapple juice
and	water.	Stir
in
crushed pineapple and grated carrots.
Pour into
mold or 10-inch Corning Ware dish. Refrigerate until firm.

title: jimmy cake
directions: Place ingredients in an oblong baking pan.
Do not stir.
Bake in oven at 225° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and add other ingredients.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Into a punch bowl, pour the pineapple juice, white soda and champagne or sparkling grape juice.
Add ice cubes.
Stir.
Makes one punch bowl full.

title: garlic chips
directions: Heat to boiling.
Pour over sliced cukes.
Add a clove of garlic in each jar; seal.

title: old timey pickles
directions: Pack fresh cucumbers in jars.
To each quart, add sugar and salt.
Fill each jar 3/4 full of vinegar.
Finish filling with water.
Seal.
Place jars in a cold water bath; bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; tighten lids.

title: beef brisket and barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil for five minutes.

title: cream of clam soup
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into saucepan and heat at low temperature.
Do not boil or soup will curdle.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and Cool Whip together.
Pour into graham cracker or chocolate crusts. Freeze. Makes two 9-inch pies.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over pie.

title: easy chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add chips.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until center is set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: gingerbread coffee cake
directions: Add to remaining mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes in greased and floured 8-inch square pan.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cover summer squash with onion in small amount of boiling salted water until crisp-tender.
Drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion. Melt butter; toss with stuffing mix.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° until heated through, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bacon and egg strata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and milk until foamy; set aside.
Place bread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Put bacon, mushrooms and onion over cheese.
Pour egg mixture over and let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until crispy.
Egg mixture should be firm.

title: mississippi mud cake and frosting
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and cocoa. Beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in flour, coconut, nuts and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured sheet cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and ice with Marshmallow Creme.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Saute zucchini, onion, and garlic in 1 teaspoon of margarine for 5 minutes.
Mix all remaining ingredients until well blended. Form into six patties and brown in pam and margarine for about 3 minutes per side.
Serve with lemon and cole slaw.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box. Take cake out of oven and punch holes in cake. Then pour Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut on top of cake. Then cool. Mix Cool Whip and coconut together and spread on top of cake. Refrigerate.

title: green beans and bacon
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for about 1/2 hour.

title: lemon pudding - baked
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add lemon juice and grated rind. Beat egg yolks. Combine with milk. Strain. Combine with lemon mixture. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into oiled custard cups. Set in pan, surrounded with hot water and bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Result is a custard bottom with sponge cake topping. Serve warm.

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water at 250°, then pour over egg whites and beat until thick.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes into 1/4 inch wedges.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: mama's fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Toss fruit with whipped topping and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into lukewarm water and stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture; add flour and blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 4 hours (before rolling out).*
Use a large bowl.
Three hours before baking, shape with only enough flour to handle.
Place on greased sheet.
*Let rise 3 hours, uncovered.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Place in ovenware bowl or pan, shaping into a round or oblong loaf.
Add ketchup and several strips of uncooked bacon over loaf.
Bake uncovered at 325° until done, approximately 1 hour, depending on width of loaf.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg yolks one at a time and beat after each. Add chocolate and vanilla and mix well. Sift together salt, soda and flour. Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating well. Beat until smooth. Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour in three 8 or 9-inch pans. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool. Frost tops with the icing.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add celery, onion and pepper. Stir about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and water.
Bring to a boil. Add rice.
Stir, cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Add kidney beans and stir until heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes.
Cook with salt until barely tender.
Add a cup of thin cream and a paste made of cornstarch or flour, some celery seed and pepper.
Put a tablespoon of butter in each soup dish and fill with the soup.
Eat with oyster crackers or saltines.

title: carol's mac n' cheese
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Grease 9 x 11-inch cake pan with Pam. Dump noodles and mix milk, eggs and salt and pepper to taste. Pour over noodles.
Place cheese in and on top of noodles.
Dot with butter.
Cook 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: homestyle scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt and water.
Melt margarine or butter in large skillet over medium heat; cook and stir vegetables in margarine for 2 minutes.
Pour on egg mixture.
As mixture begins to set at bottom and side, gently lift cooked portions with spatula so that uncooked portions can flow to bottom.
Cook until eggs are thickened throughout but still moist, 3 to 5 minutes. Makes 2 large servings.
Good for a fast, last minute meal.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 3 quart saucepan.
Cook to soft-ball stage, 240° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly. Cool slightly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add one box of strawberry Jell-O while hot.
Cool and add 1 quart strawberries; put in baked pie shell.
Add Cool Whip.

title: heavenly crust peach pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar to egg whites while still beating.
Fold in soda crackers, baking powder, pecans and vanilla.
Spoon mixture into a buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Cover the sides and bottom of pan with mixture so that it looks like fat pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
When cooled, put pie shell in refrigerator overnight.

title: christmas cookies-single batch
directions: Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees in a 9 x 13 pan.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mash squash.
Mix in remainder of ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: buckwheat muffins(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar and molasses; beat until light.
Beat in eggs.
Sift baking powder, baking soda, flour and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in buckwheat groats and buttermilk.
Only stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Add nuts (optional).
Grease 2 1/2-inch deep muffin pans.
Fill 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes, until brown.

title: pastry
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add egg and water.
Mix and sprinkle vinegar over dough.
Roll up and chill before using. Makes 3 pie crust pastries.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all together.
After it starts boiling, cook 1/2 hour.

title: african stew
directions: Brown chuck; put aside.
In new pan, put in chicken; brown. Add chuck and rest of ingredients.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Put water in a pan.
Put noodles in the pan to boil.
Boil for 2 hours.
When they are done, put the mix on it.
Stir 3 times and eat.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage in a large skillet or saucepan.
Cook over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour. Cook over medium heat about 6 minutes.
Stir in milk. Add seasonings.
Cook until thick.
Spoon over biscuits.

title: seafood fancy
directions: In a large bowl, mix all but shrimp and crab.
Add crabmeat and mix well.
Add shrimp and mix well.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor or blender until fairly smooth.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with any cold seafood.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in a pan; add Rice-A-Roni and brown.
Add 2 cups hot water, soup and season packet.
Mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish; place chicken on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cook in microwave for 2 minutes; stir, 2 minutes, stir and then 2 more minutes.
Store in airtight container for freshness.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Simmer the first 8 ingredients in covered saucepan for 25 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to soup, cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Melt Velveeta.
Drain jar of pimiento; add to cheese.
Mix in Miracle Whip and sugar.
May need more Miracle Whip and sugar to taste.
Can be served on bread, with crackers or vegetables.

title: apricot trifle
directions: Line sides of a 6 to 8 cup glass bowl with cake slices, cut about 1/4-inch thick.
Drain apricots, reserving 1/3 cup juice. Mix juice with sherry; drizzle over cake.
Set aside several apricot halves for garnish.
Measure custard powder into 4 cup measure.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Blend in sugar, almond extract, orange rind, raisins and almonds. Microwave at High 5 minutes, stirring once.
Microwave at High 2 minutes more, or until mixture boils and thickens.
Cool.
Gently stir in apricots.
Pour over pound cake slices in bowl.
Chill.

title: homemade chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan heat milk and mix together the remaining ingredients well.
When milk is heated, add the mixed ingredients. Cook until thick.
When thick, pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes in a preheated oven.

title: holiday cranberry punch(diabetic)
directions: Mix Crystal Light fruit drink mix according to package directions.
Add equal amount of sugar-free cranberry juice. Freeze in wide mouth containers.
Thaw slightly (about 1 hour before serving time) to a slush consistency.
Combine with chilled sugar-free 7-Up in punch bowl.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: purple passion
directions: Add all ingredients, blend and enjoy.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Cook
onion
and garlic in hot oil until tender but not brown. Stir
in
the
next 8 ingredients, simmer uncovered 30 minutes; remove bay leaf.
Add Italian Meat Balls and continue
cooking
30 minutes
longer.
Serve
over
hot spaghetti. Makes 6 servings.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Cook meat and drain real good.
Cube cheese and stir into meat until melted.
Add oregano and garlic (minced or salt) to taste. Spread on rye cocktail bread.
Place on cookie sheet and place in freezer on cookie sheets until frozen.
Then remove and place on foil in Tupperware containers and return to freezer until ready to use.
When ready to serve, place directly from freezer to oven. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or microwave 1 minute or perhaps more, depending on oven.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix with fork until moistened.
Press into a pie pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Makes one 8 or 9-inch crust (8 servings).

title: brownie cake
directions: Melt oleo, cocoa, oil and water.
Pour on sugar, flour and vanilla; stir.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add sour milk; stir well. Pour into well greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Frost cake while hot.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Combine other ingredients in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place a layer of cracker crumbs, then a layer of oysters.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Repeat layers, having top layer cracker crumbs.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until brown.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Rinse beans.
Combine beans and water in Dutch oven.
Cover and boil 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Let stand 1 hour or overnight.
Add salt.
Simmer, partially covered, for 1 hour, or until beans are tender.
Drain, reserving 3/4 cup of liquid.
Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Combine uncooked bacon, brown sugar, molasses, onion and dry mustard in slow cooker.
Add 3/4 cup reserved liquid.
Cover; cook on low for 10 hours or on high for 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fresh cauliflower mimosa(serves 4)
directions: Place cauliflower in saucepan in 1-inch of boiling water with juice of 1/2 lemon; cook until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain and place on serving platter.
Sprinkle cauliflower with margarine and remaining lemon juice.
Combine Parmesan cheese and paprika; sprinkle over cauliflower.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Top with sieved egg and parsley.
Contains 110 calories per serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar and spices; mix lightly through apples.
Heap into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with butter. Cover with top crust which has slits cut in it.
Seal; bake 50 to 60 minutes until crust is browned and apples are cooked.

title: chicken "crescent" casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water and salt and pepper until done. Take chicken off bones.
Put a large piece of chicken on large end of roll and roll it up.
Line in casserole dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese sit out for 2 to 3 hours.
Mix all other ingredients except nuts.
Roll into a ball.
Place nuts on waxed paper and roll cheese ball over this to cover in nuts. Refrigerate.

title: turkey noodle encore
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain and place noodles in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with turkey and broccoli. Sprinkle half of the cheese.
Blend soup and water.
Pour over noodles, turkey and broccoli.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with French fried onions.

title: cheese pasta in a pot
directions: Brown ground beef. Add onion, garlic, Ragu sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms. Simmer for 20 minutes. Cook shells.

title: toffee candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil; brush foil with margarine. Place margarine, sugar and water in large skillet. Cook on high until the mixture turns the color of coffee with cream. Stir continuously. Pour onto foil-lined cookie sheet. Sprinkle the chocolate chips on top and spread around. When hard, break into pieces.

title: dill dip
directions: Using a spatula, combine all ingredients in a medium bowl. Serve chilled with assorted vegetables, crackers and cheese cubes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Beat
sugar,
lemon
juice, flour, cornstarch and eggs. Add some lemon rind.
Spread over baked layer and bake at 350° for 20 minutes
or
until set.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Add all ingredients to beaten eggs.
Beat until smooth. Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Pour thin layer of batter onto sheet.
Bake at 275° until done.

title: cheese-broccoli soup
directions: In large pot, saute onion in oil for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes; boil until cubes dissolve. Add noodles and boil uncovered for 3 minutes. Stri in broccoli, salt and garlic.
Cook 4 minutes. Add milk, cheese and pepper.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble on paper towel. Finely chop broccoli and onion; toss with raisins and sunflower seeds.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and add.
Mix in crumbled bacon last.
This salad will keep for days in the refrigerator.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add oil and eggs.
Beat; add carrots and beat well.
Bake in 3 layers at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: martha washington chocolates
directions: Melt margarine, add other ingredients, mix, roll in balls, dip in chocolate mixture.
Let set in refrigerator 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hot corn
directions: Mix together well and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add chicken, onion and salt.
Toss.
Add remaining ingredients, except whipping cream.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
Add whipped cream just before serving.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon, stirring frequently, approximately 4 minutes. Drain.
Add potatoes and water.
Simmer until potatoes are cooked, approximately 15 minutes.
Add corn and evaporated milk.
Salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: better than ? cake
directions: Mix and bake in a 13 x 9-inch rectangular pan as directed on package.
When cake is done, mix sugar and undrained pineapple in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; let cool some.
Poke holes in cake with a fork.
Pour pineapple mixture over it.
Prepare pudding as directed on package, then pour pudding over pineapple layer and refrigerate.
Before serving, cover with whipping cream and coconut and/or nuts.

title: corn pudding
directions: In medium mixing bowl, beat eggs lightly, add corn and flour. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Set dish in a baking pan that contains a bit of hot water.
Bake at 350°
for about 75 minutes. In the first 10 to 15 minutes of cooking, stir several times.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Marinate for 24 hours. Keeps 3 weeks.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil in saucepan; remove from heat.
Cool.
Slice dill pickles very thin.
Place celery seed in pickle jar.
Return sliced pickles to jar.
Pour cooled vinegar mixture over pickles.
Chill in refrigerator for 3 days before serving, inverting jar several times.
Store in refrigerator. Yield:
30 servings.

title: red plum bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add beaten eggs. Mix well. Add plums and food coloring. Sift together all dry ingredients; add to other mixture and blend well. Add nuts last. May be cooked in a Bundt pan and a loaf pan or 4 loaf pans. Grease and flour pans and pour batter in. Cook at 350° in oven for 1 hour. Test with toothpick. If it comes out clean, the bread is done.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Mix the rest of ingredients thoroughly then pour over first layer and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: robert snooks ("snookie") colonial bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Let stand until lukewarm (about 30 minutes).
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 10 minutes, then add to first mixture.
Add rye and whole wheat flour.
Stir thoroughly.
Add unbleached flour and mix until dough leaves sides of bowl.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut and save juice.
Add enough vinegar to make 1 cup. Put 1 1/4 cups sugar into vinegar-juice mixture. Bring to a boil. Pour hot juice over other ingredients.
Mix well.
Let the mixture stand in refrigerator at least overnight.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Cream margarine with oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk, then add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Bring all of the above but the parsley to a boil and boil for one minute.
Simmer for one hour, stirring occasionally.
Add 2 tsp. parsley and stir before serving.
Makes 10-12 servings.
Freezes well.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: In a small bowl, combine caramel topping, chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread in the bottom of frozen pie crust.
In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Spread over the caramel mixture.
Bake at 400° on preheated baking sheet for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: perfection cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, water with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Stir in sour cream, chocolate chips, pecans, grated chocolate and coconut.
Bake at 300° in well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and line with wax paper a 7 x 11-inch pan.
This will make a thick cake.
You may also use any size or make cupcakes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Stir.
Pour over seasoned ribs or chicken that have been slightly browned in 325° oven.
Bake until vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes.
Do not cover. Sauce thickens as it is being cooked.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, garlic, mayonnaise, lemon juice, dry mustard and Tabasco.
Fold in crab meat and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve with broken bread pieces or on top of crackers.

title: cocoa candy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Cook 2 minutes.
Take off stove and add peanut butter, oatmeal and nuts.
Stir good and put in pan to cool.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole bowl, mix onion, broth, boned chicken, cheese and rice.
Cover. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat egg and buttermilk together.
Combine dry ingredients and add chopped onion.
Blend in egg and buttermilk mixture.
Heat oil to 370°.
Drop batter in small balls into hot oil.
Fry until evenly browned.
Drain on paper towels and serve at once.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: snowball oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together, then add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients including the oats.
Gradually add this to the first mixture, a cup at a time, until well blended.
Chill in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll into small balls (1 teaspoon), then roll in the powdered sugar.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: turkey black bean chili
directions: In a large pot, cook turkey and onion in oil over medium-high heat, stirring to break up lumps, until turkey is no longer pink, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain off any excess fat.

title: brian's tex-mex dip
directions: Spread beans on bottom of large pan.
Add salsa.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning well.
Spread mixture as next layer. Sprinkle layers of olives, onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: grandma florence kline's spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and lard.
Add eggs and mix.
Add salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix.
Add soda to milk.
Rinse out measuring cup with a little water.
Add to the mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: baked sauerkraut
directions: Brown Smok-Y-Links in Dutch oven.
Remove Smok-Y-Links and place sauerkraut in Dutch oven.
Put Smok-Y-Links on top of sauerkraut.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt.
Cook for one minute after bringing to full rolling boil.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool until firm.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix with cream cheese, soup, ketchup and milk.
Mix well and pour into greased 2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly in center.
Top with canned or homemade biscuits and bake until brown. Serves 6-8.

title: ed pack's texas chili
directions: Fry suet in cast-iron kettle until crisp.
Add cubed beef, about 1 pound at a time, and brown, stirring as it cooks.
Remove each
pound after browning.
When all the meat is browned, return it to kettle and add seasonings and stock (or broth).
D not add salt at this time.
Cover and simmer for two hours.
Skim off fat. Combine cornmeal with cold water and stir into chili.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add salt to taste just before serving.
Makes about 3 3/4 quarts.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Line pan with foil.
Place brisket in pan.
Use salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Pour liquid smoke over all.
Cut up butter and place on top of brisket.
Cook at 325° all day until tender.
About 1 hour before you are ready to serve, pour barbecue sauce over and return to oven and cook 1 hour.
Cool and slice.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients, except noodles.
When ready to bake, fold in 3/4 of the noodles.
Remaining noodles are for the top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 3-inch pan.
Dump layer of pineapple, pie filling and dry cake mix.
Top with margarine and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cool, Cool Whip can be top layer.

title: apricot slices
directions: Pour melted butter over all ingredients, except apricots, and mix well.
Set aside 1 cup of mix for top.
Put on cookie sheet (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch), next filling (apricots), then rest of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut when still a little warm

title: furniture polish
directions: Heat all together in pan.
Stir in honey.
Do not allow to scorch.
Take as hot as you can stand!

title: french bread monterey
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread over cut sides of bread. Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil with medium flame until brown or bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Quickly saute chicken in hot vegetable oil.
Turn heat down to medium and add mushrooms.
Mix 1 tablespoon soy sauce, onion powder and ginger.
Add to chicken in frying pan.
Mix cornstarch, remaining soy sauce and reserved pineapple juice.
Add to chicken and stir until thickened.
Add water if desired for thinner sauce. Add pineapple and oranges just before serving.
Serve over hot white rice.

title: turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Mix can of chicken soup and a can of water with the stock in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil slowly, stirring until well blended.
Pour 2 cups over bread crumbs; stir well.
Let soak until well blended and no lumps.
Saute onions and celery in a small saucepan, using 1/4 cup of stock.
(Do not brown or burn.) Cook until tender, but not done.
Add to soaked bread crumbs.
Add poultry seasoning, sage and pepper; mix well, adding additional stock to make a very loose dressing mix.
Grease a deep casserole dish with the butter.
Pour dressing in and bake in a preheated oven at 350° until done and brown on top and bottom.
(The dressing can be stirred in the oven one time to assure even cooking by loosening up the sides that cook and brown fast.)

title: christmas morn casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves approximately 10.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix everything until lumpy.
Spread over apples.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender or top is golden brown.

title: ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on pan; bake until brown, about 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: frozen peanut butter pie(easy!)
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla on medium speed until well blended. Gently stir in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or over night. Serve frozen.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in saucepan.
Saute garlic until golden brown. Stir in basil, parsley and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soup, milk and spices in a 3 quart baking dish. Stir in chicken and vegetables. Bake 15 minutes at 400° until mixture begins to bubble.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt margarine; saute onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup ripe olives, chilies, sour cream and soup.
Mix well.
Save 3/4 cup sauce; set aside. Fold in chicken and 1/2 cup cheese to remaining sauce.
Warm tortillas as directions on package say.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture; roll up.
Place seam side down in ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, combine 3/4 cup reserved sauce and milk.
Spoon over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and olives.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello	in
boiling
water.
Add
strawberries, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour	1/2 of this mixture in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Chill.
Spread
on sour cream and add remaining jello mixture.
Chill until firm.
Serves about 16.

title: poached pears
directions: Fill 3-quart saucepan 1/3 full of water.
Add orange peel, cloves and cinnamon.
Bring to light boil for 5 to 10 minutes. Add pears and Port; cover and continue at a light boil for 15 minutes or until pears are tender.
Serve with Port sauce.

title: roast chicken
directions: Cut up celery. Season chicken with seasonings. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: faith's easy cheese and pepperoni bread
directions: Let bread rise.
Roll dough 1/2-inch in thickness.
Place layer of cheese on dough, then place layer of pepperoni on cheese. Spread on pizza sauce.
Repeat with cheese, pepperoni and sauce until you reach the desired thickness.
Roll into loaf pan (oblong).
Tuck ends in before baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lime pineapple with cheese balls
directions: Drain can of sliced pineapple.
Fill with jello mix.
Chill. When set, slice between slices.
Place slices on lettuce.
Make cream cheese balls; roll in nuts or serve pineapple slices with sour cream and mayonnaise dressing.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Boil 1/2 minute only cocoa, sugar and milk.
Stir in peanut butter, butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto a buttered pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook California mix as directed and drain.
Add celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix and put in casserole.
Mix oleo, cheese and cracker crumbs and spread over top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken huntington
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 20 but can be made into smaller casserole dishes and frozen for later menus.

title: delicious one-dish dinner
directions: Peel potatoes; wash and slice.
Grease casserole with butter. Put potatoes, carrots and onions in layers.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put dabs of butter over top.
Next, make hamburger patties; put on top.
Add a little water.
Cover and bake one hour at 350°.

title: poppy seed mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except poppy seed, in blender.
Blend for 1 minute.
Add poppy seed and blend a few seconds.
Dressing will have a green color.
May be stored in refrigerator as long as 3 weeks.

title: applesauce-oatmeal cake
directions: Bring applesauce to a boil in a small saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in oats and raisins; cover and let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg and beat well. Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and ground cloves. Gradually add to creamed mixture; mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in applesauce mixture.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.
Makes 9 servings.

title: fresh fruit crepes(a memorable, elegant dessert!)
directions: Mix the batter well by a whisk or blender, then let it rest 2 hours before use.
Make crepes in a crepe pan or skillet the size you like.
I make 6-inch crepes for this fruit recipe.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Soak bread in cold water; add other ingredients, except chops. Put stuffing on chop.
Cover with another chop.
Repeat until all chops are used.
Tie with string so the chops will stand as if in a roast.
Roast at 350° until chops are done, about 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour large tube pan.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese, sugar and flavorings until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Stir in flour, adding 1 cup of pecans to last portion of flour.

title: crispy chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in two pieces, discarding the tips.
In a small shallow bowl, combine butter and garlic powder.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken wings into butter, then crumb mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Yields about 20 appetizers.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add oil, then add other ingredients as listed.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet (I use Pam).
Bake 9 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit juice sweetened banana bread
directions: Mix bananas, egg and milk.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, soda and walnuts.
Add apple juice, butter and banana mixture and stir together until well blended.
Bake at 350° in a greased bread pan for 45 to 55 minutes (if using a glass dish, reduce heat by 25°).
When toothpick comes out clean, it is done.
Do not overbake.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, milk, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Roll in ball and roll in crushed corn flakes.
Put cherry in middle.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: *hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, beating in thoroughly.
Sift flour with baking powder and stir into egg mixture.
Add milk, shortening, salt and extracts.
Mix quickly and turn into an 8-inch square greased pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for about 30 minutes. Remove from oven and invert pan for 1 hour or until cake is cold. Sprinkle powdered sugar over the top.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Combine pancake mix and beer.
Peel sweet onions and slice into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Separate into rings.
Dip into batter and fry in deep fat.
Drain and sprinkle with salt.

title: plum quick bread
directions: Grease 2 (9 x 5) loaves.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
Bring to boil and cook 3 minutes (gradually). Add hot syrup to eggs, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange pecans on filling.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until set.
Cool.

title: chunkies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Drop on plastic or wax paper.
Cool.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt butter.
Add to remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls.
Chill and then dip in chocolate.

title: speedy beet borscht
directions: In a large pan, pour liquid from the can of beets.
Grate the beets and put in pan, along with 2 cans water.
Add lemon juice, sugar and salt and bring to a fast boil.
Allow Borscht to cool and refrigerate.
Add a dollop of sour cream (or yogurt) to individual bowls.

title: holiday tea(hot drink)
directions: Combine dry mix; use one rounded teaspoonful per cup of boiling water.
Makes enough for 12 quarts tea.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop from spoon
onto
greased	cookie	sheet.	Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Combine all ingredients. Heat.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Add soda to water.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Blend in mincemeat.
Add flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: gelatin cloud salad
directions: Combine sour cream, Cool Whip and dry Jell-O thoroughly.
Add fruit and marshmallows; chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Over medium heat, stir soup until smooth.
Gradually add milk. In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions and sauce.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour; uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Combine chicken pieces, water, onion, sherry, curry powder, salt and celery.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Cool; remove chicken. Strain and reserve broth.
Remove skin and bones from chicken. Cut in bite-size pieces.
Saute mushrooms in butter; drain.
Add water to broth and boil wild rice until tender; don't drain.
Mix with chicken, mushrooms, mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour into 4-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange chicken salad
directions: Toss with olive oil/balsamic/herb dressing to taste.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour and cocoa together.
Gradually add to other mixture.
Stir just enough to mix.
Add nuts and vanilla; stir.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brenda's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas.
Chill.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: buttermilk glaze
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in pan and bring to a boil. Cook for 4 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove and add vanilla. This glaze is especially good on pound cake or yellow cake.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, butter and milk together.
Pour over partially baked cake.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over caramel layer.
Top with remaining cake batter and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix well.
Use 1 teaspoon cookie dough for each cookie and roll into ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 8 minutes.
Take from oven and place 1 Hershey's Kiss in the center of each cookie.
Put back into oven for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: indian corn
directions: Cook onion in margarine for a few minutes.
Add ground beef and salt and cook until beef changes color.
Add corn and tomato sauce.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamy chicken spoleto
directions: Saute green pepper in margarine. Blend in flour and herb spice mix from spaghetti mix.
Gradually add milk. Stir constantly until thickened.
Add chicken.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: oreo icebox cake(no baking)
directions: Put crumbled Oreos in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 10x sugar, peanut butter and milk in a large mixer bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mix over Oreos.
Put chopped nuts (or crushed Oreos) on top.
Freeze it.
Defrost slightly before serving.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes until good and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green chili rice
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft. Combine all other ingredients (except 1 c. of cheese) in a lightly greased baking dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled onions
directions: Scald onions in boiling water for 2 minutes, then cover with cold water.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add cold water and cover.
Let stand for 12 hours.
Drain, rinse and drain.
Combine sugar, mustard seed and vinegar and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pack onions into hot, sterile jars.
Place 1 hot red pepper and 1 bay leaf in each jar.
Pour boiling liquid over onions to 1/8 inch from top. Quickly seal each jar.
Makes 3 pints.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Grease a large baking sheet.
Place the raisins in a small bowl, cover with hot water.
Allow to soak for 10 minutes.
In a large bowl combine to oats, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. In a medium bowl combine the egg, Crisco, honey, vanilla, sugar and brown sugar.
Add to the oats.
Stir to mix well.
Drain the raisins and stir into the bowl.
Drop the dough by tablespoon onto the prepared baking sheet.
Allow 2 inch space between them.
Bake at 350 for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: black bean chili
directions: Saute onion in the oil. Combine all ingredients.
Cover pan and simmer 20 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans and toss lightly.
Heat oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper until dissolved.
Cool and pour over beans.
Add onion and toss lightly again.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place
sauerkraut loosely in 10-inch pie plate;
sprinkle with seed,
cup cheese, dressing, pastrami and rest of cheese. Toss bread crumbs in butter and sprinkle over cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ethel's vanilla custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla together, after fully blended, pour into a 8 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Lightly sprinkle top with nutmeg (optional),
Place in a preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes, until nothing sticks to a knife when inserted into the custard,
remove from oven when custard has fully set. After fully chilled, cut and serve as 3 x 3 inch squares.
Keep refrigerated.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: play dough
directions: Mix and cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from pan. Knead slightly.
Store in airtight containers.
(Please do not eat.)

title: date balls
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to boil (bubbling) and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies.
Form into balls. Roll in coconut.

title: bean patties
directions: Mash beans well with fork.
Beat egg and add to mashed beans. Include chopped onions and pepper, if available.
Shape into round patties and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in 2 tablespoons of fat until brown on both sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a buttered shallow dish.
Pour water over apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix butter, sugar and flour until crumbly.
Spread over apple mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: deluxe baked spinach
directions: Cook flour, milk and onion until smooth and thickened.
Add spinach, eggs and nutmeg and season with salt and pepper.
Turn into buttered casserole and top with a mixture of shredded cheese and bread or cracker crumbs.
Drizzle butter over the top and bake in a 375° oven for about 15 - 20 min.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix sugars, butter and cream.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add marshmallows and vanilla;
add powdered sugar.
This goes well on jam cakes, spice and apple cakes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put salt, shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Pour in boiling water; blend and allow to cool.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
Shape dough into rolls using very little flour on hands.
