Place rolls on greased baking sheet and let rise until doubled in 1 to 2 hours. Bake at 425° until lightly browned.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown beef in fat.
Add onions.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add water, vegetables and seasonings; mix.
Boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes more.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Rub with fingers until crumbly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or longer at 350°.

title: dried beef and noodle casserole
directions: Saute beef.
Add flour, milk and cheese.
Add mushroom soup, pimento and noodles (cooked).
Put in casserole; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake for 1/2 to 3/4 hour in a 350° oven.

title: chili
directions: Cook pinto beans ahead of time.
Fry ground beef, onions and green pepper until well done.
Add to beans, ground beef and chili powder.
As you add the tomato paste, add 2 cans of water also. Add tomato sauce and another can of water.
Mix together well and cook on low for about 1 hour.
Salt to taste.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop apples and nuts; place in refrigerator to chill.
Boil cranberries and sugar for 2 minutes or until the cranberry skins start to open.
Dissolve cherry Jell-O with one cup boiling water. Combine Jell-O, cranberries, apples, nuts and the juice of one orange.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to box directions.
As soon as cake comes out of oven, make holes in it with handle of wooden spoon; pour Eagle milk over cake, then pour chocolate syrup over top. Let cool and refrigerate.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown hamburger meat with some onions.
Add okra and tomatoes. Cook slow until tender, then add instant rice.
(I put a little tomato juice in mine.)

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together all ingredients and press into a greased 8 x 8 pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: turkey meatball stroganoff
directions: Combine turkey, crushed croutons and garlic powder.
Form into balls.
Spray large skillet with Pam.
Brown turkey balls on all sides.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
In the same skillet, cook the onions until tender in 2 tablespoons liquid Butter Buds. Add the mushrooms and flour.
Stir in chicken broth and seasoning mix (Weight Watchers Brand) and water.
Boil.
Return the turkey to the pan and heat but do not boil.
Simmer, uncovered, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in yogurt, but do not boil.
Serve turkey balls and sauce over cooked noodles.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add cheese; stir and remove from heat. In another pot, dissolve chicken cubes in water; add bay leaf and boil.
Add broccoli; cook until tender.
Do not drain.
Blend in cheese sauce.

title: dang good pie
directions: Melt butter and add all remaining ingredients.
Pour filling in pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until set and brown.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: In a bowl, mix cream cheese, vanilla and coconut flavoring. Add salt.
Add coconut, then powdered sugar.
Work it in your hands to the consistency where it forms a ball.
Form into balls and let dry on wax paper to set.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: cassoulet de castelnaudary
directions: Place beans in boiling water to cover with 2 teaspoons of salt.
Boil 2 minutes; let stand 1 hour.
Skim, then half-cook.

title: date bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, flour, salt, dates, and nuts.
Bake in 10 x 13 pan.
Cook 325° for 30 minutes or until firm and light brown.
Do not over cook.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potato.
Cut in small or 4 pieces; boil until done.
Drain water off.
Add the sugar, small amount at a time.
It will become thin, then thicken.
When like pie dough, roll out on wax paper with sugar sprinkled on it.
Spread the peanut butter on it and roll up like jelly roll.

title: wassail
directions: Bring first 8 ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven.
Reduce heat and cook stirring occasionally 15 - 20 min., add orange slices and serve immediately.
Yield:
1 gallon.
May be placed in crock pot to keep warm.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter with brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix to make a crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining into bottom of 8 to 9-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef.
Add salt, garlic salt and oregano.
Add tomato sauce and paste plus 2 each cans of water.
Simmer about 3 hours. (I use crock-pot).
Boil 1 package lasagna noodles in large pan of water and salt.
Put 1 tablespoon oil in water to keep noodles from sticking together.
Boil about 20 minutes.
Drain noodles.
Arrange in dish or pan in the following order:
Cover bottom of dish with sauce.
Then layer of noodles.
Then layer of Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Repeat until finished (2 layers).
Make sure to have cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add vegetables and sprinkle with sugar and salt.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring twice during cooking period.
(If you like vegetables well done, cook longer.)

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Make pie crust as instructions state. In a large mixing bowl, add Bisquick, oil, cheese, onion, eggs, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Stir until mixed well.
Add zucchini. Stir until all zucchini is covered.
Place in cooled pie crust. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean from center.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Mix well;
press
in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (let cool).

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir together sugar and oil.
Stir in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients (flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon).
Add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts, vanilla and apples.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: home-made crab cakes
directions: Chop the first four (4) ingredients very fine.
Add the toast (crumbled up), crab meat, egg (beaten), and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Shape into 8 patties.
Bread with cracker meal. Fry in large frying pan;
Turning until browned all over.

title: fun cones
directions: Follow the directions on a package of cake mix as if you're making cupcakes.
Instead of filling cupcake papers, fill the ice cream cones 3/4 of the way full.
Bake as directed for cupcakes. After they have cooled, decorate the tops with icing and add gumdrops, sprinkles or candy.

title: smoked ranch beans
directions: Do not drain beans.
Mix together all ingredients and cook in a slow cooker for several hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt, pepper and flour round steak. Beat with meat tenderizer (knife) until flour is beaten in.
Brown the meat in oil. Add onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and boiling water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets well. Combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Combine egg, water and vanilla.
Set aside.

Blend brown sugar and Puritan oil in a large bowl at low speed of electric mixer. Add egg mixture. Beat until smooth. Add flour mixture in 3 parts at lowest speed. Scrape bowl well after each addition. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 7 or 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on baking sheets 1 minute. Remove to cooling rack.
Serves 12.

title: grandma's old time molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar, vanilla and shortening together.
Add molasses and coffee.
Sift flour, soda, spices and salt together.
Add to other mixed ingredients.
Chill.
Roll out and cut.
Bake in 350° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine cooked squash and add other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into greased dish and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: easy oven baked potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onions 1/4-inch slices slightly overlapping in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine next 5 ingredients and drizzle over potatoes and onions.
Bake 40 minutes at 400° covered. Uncover, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes uncovered.

title: denver biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with enough flour for batter.
Let set 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and enough flour for a soft dough.
Put in a warm place to rise.
Then roll out on floured board.
Cut out and let rise and bake.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.
Bake as may as you need at a time.

title: mandarin orange-pineapple cake
directions: Combine and mix well the cake mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans; will make 4 (9-inch) round layers.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Cool layers.
Mix pudding mix with Cool Whip.
Add pineapple.
Beat until reaches spreading consistency.
Ice layers and sides of cake.
If this cake lasts more than 3 days, refrigerate.

title: marinated black-eyed pea salad
directions: Reserve bacon and lettuce.
Marinate all other ingredients for 4 hours in refrigerator.
Drain salad and line bowl with lettuce leaves; add salad and garnish with crumbled bacon.
May be marinated overnight in refrigerator.

title: russian cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 45-55 minutes.
Preferable to make the cake in a bundt pan.

title: creamy chicken-rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions on package.
Cook onion in butter till tender.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Drain mushrooms and keep liquid.
Add enough chicken broth to make 1 1/2 cups with mushroom liquid.
Gradually stir into flour mixture. Add cream.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add rice, mushrooms, chicken, pimento, parsley, salt and pepper.
Place in 2 quart buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until almost crisp.
Wrap bacon around chestnuts and secure with toothpicks.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chestnuts.
Bake 45 minutes.
Makes about 24 appetizers.

title: cow pies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oil in microwave, stirring until smooth.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper.
Chill until firm.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cover eggs with boiling water in a saucepan and let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Plunge eggs into cold water to keep yolks from discoloring and to make shells remove easier.
Cut hard-boiled eggs into halves lengthwise.
Combine egg yolks and Miracle Whip, then add sweet relish.
Fill white halves with egg yolk mixture and sprinkle with paprika, if you wish to.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, jello and red food coloring.
Arrange fresh strawberries on cooked pie shell.
Pour cooled filling over fruit and chill.
Add whipped topping.

title: macaroni supreme
directions: Cook elbow macaroni 7 to 10 minutes, brown the ground beef. Take a Pyrex dish.
Layer sauce, macaroni, American cheese, etc. Bake in oven at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at the time, beating well.
Sift flour and cocoa together and blend with creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans. Pour in square pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Bake in bread pans at 325° for 1 hour or more.

title: enchilada dip
directions: Layer in order on a serving platter.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: almond tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water.
When cool, add enough cold water to make 1 gallon.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: count down brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour sifted with cocoa, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover with marshmallows; return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting. Cut into squares and serve.

title: raspberry almond tart
directions: Blend together flour, almonds, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or fingertips until coarse crumbs form.
Blend together egg and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture; combine well until dough is formed.
Wrap and refrigerate dough for 30 minutes.
Roll out 1/3 of dough to 10 x 4-inch rectangle between two sheets of wax paper.
Place on cookie sheet in freezer.
Roll out remaining 2/3 dough to 11 inch circle between two sheets of wax paper.
Press into bottom and sides of a 10-inch tart pan, forming a 1/2-inch deep shell.
Spread raspberry jam on dough in pan to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Cut 1/2 inch strips of dough from rectangle in freezer.
Crisscross strips about 1 inch apart on top of raspberry preserves to form lattice top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fat mama's egg nog
directions: Separate egg whites from egg yellows.
Beat egg yellows until thick and lemon-yellow.
Add pre-measured whiskey little by little while beating yellows.
Set aside to season.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar little by little.
Whip the cream until firm.
Stir in whites, then yellows.
Mix slowly but well.
If you desire, add a dash of ground cinnamon.
Serves 6.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add rice, onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture is lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Quickly bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water; stir until jello is dissolved, then add sliced strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Mix well and pour 1/2 of mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm, then spread over chilled jello 1 pint of sour cream.
Cover with remaining jello mixture and chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.
Garnish with 1 teaspoon of sour cream.

title: old fashioned light fruitcake
directions: Use 2 loaf pans, or 1 tube pan, or miniature pans.
Line pans with foil.

title: pork chops and zucchini
directions: In a large plastic bag, combine flour, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, salt, dill weed and pepper.
Place pork chops in bag and shake to coat.
Shake off excess flour and reserve.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat; brown pork chops on both sides. Reduce heat.
Place onion slices on chops.
Add water to skillet. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Place zucchini slices over the onion.
Mix remaining Parmesan cheese with reserved flour mixture. Sprinkle over zucchini.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until pork chops are tender.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
In large kettle add hamburger and onion to potatoes and carrots, water.
Cook until veggies are tender.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat.

title: 3 bean hamburger casserole
directions: Fry bacon; brown hamburger with onions and garlic.
Drain. Mix beans with liquids; add all other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Ketchup to your taste is optional.

title: cold pea salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and serve in bowl lined with red leaf lettuce.
Garnish with sliced red onion rings and bacon bits.

title: german chop suey
directions: Brown the meat lightly.
Saute celery and onion.
Cook spaghetti until just done.
Combine all and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cayenne corn bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
In a medium-sized bowl, lightly beat the eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the butter; mix well.

Melt 1 tablespoon of the butter and stir it into the batter. Place the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter in a large cast-iron skillet or a 9-inch square baking pan and place in the oven until the butter melts.
Immediately pour the batter into the pan.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown and the center is firm.
Makes 6 to 9 servings.

title: cold pack pickles
directions: In
large
jars
gallon size), put good amount of dill, 1/4
of
an
onion, sliced, 3 cloves of garlic, 5 green mustang grapes and 5 leaves, 3 tablespoons canning salt and 8 tablespoons of
vinegar.
Fill jars with slightly warm water. Add
hot pepper to each jar, if desired.
Close tight with used
jar
lids. Shake
jar by tilting over several times for salt
to dissolve. Place filled jars on platters because they will
seep
while fermentation is in process.
Ready to eat in about

These will not keep longer than 4 months.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain green beans, wax and garbanzo beans.
Drain and rinse kidney beans.
Chop green pepper and onion.
Put beans, green pepper and onion in bowl.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over bean mixture.
Mix until coated.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: stuffed halibut
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
To make bread stuffing, saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons water to moisten.
Rinse halibut.
Lay one fillet, skin down, in margarine-coated baking dish.
Cover with bread stuffing.
Lay second fillet on top of the stuffing and press down firmly.
Secure with toothpicks.
Coat top of fish with margarine.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 servings.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Add ground beef, if desired. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Place half of the spaghetti noodles in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of vegetable-beef mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix the soup and water until smooth; pour over casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients and pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
until done.

title: butternut cake
directions: (Start in a cold oven.) Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs one at
a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, water and flavoring.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 40 minutes at 350°.

title: diane's squash casserole
directions: Chop squash and onion.
Boil until tender and drain.
Combine all other ingredients.
Top with crackers and melted margarine. Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken de provence
directions: Cut each breast in half.
Dredge in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Saute breasts in butter until lightly brown.
Add garlic, sliced scallions and mushrooms for 10 minutes.
Add herbs de provence.
Then add juice of lemon, wine and stock.
Simmer for 20 minutes until done.

title: crab pizza
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients until fairly smooth; spread on plate or pizza pan.
Top with the remaining ingredients.
Dip crackers into this.
Works best when dip is near room temperature. Makes about 1 (10-inch) plate and 1 (6-inch) plate.

title: cranberry gelatin mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cranberry sauce.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into four cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar and mayonnaise; pour over other ingredients and chill.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix together mayonnaise or salad dressing, sugar, vinegar and onion. Add broccoli and bacon.

title: oatmeal crackers
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Roll thin.
Cut in any shape you like. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: easy bake cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: super brownies
directions: Add nuts if desired.

title: fresh apple cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in 9-inch square or 11 x 7-inch baking pan at 450°.

title: maw-maw ruth's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, Crisco and peanut butter.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour, soda and salt. Blend well. Shape into balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 320° for 5 to 12 minutes. Caution:
Do not double!

title: chili pie
directions: Brown ground beef and saute onion.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and chili seasoning.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add beans (drained).
Pour this on the layer of corn chips and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spider cookies
directions: In the top of a double boiler, melt the butterscotch bits together with the peanut butter.
Remove from heat, stir in marshmallows and hard noodles.
Spoon (cookie size) onto cookie sheets and refrigerate until hard.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Mix together the soup, cheese, eggs, mayonnaise and onion; add to broccoli.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with cheese crackers.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: kale with tomato and onion
directions: Remove stems from kale.
Wash leaves thoroughly (do not dry). Tear into small pieces.
Place wet kale into a large Dutch oven (do not add water).
Cook, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.

title: baked pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, brown the chops and drain on absorbent paper.
On the bottom of a buttered 2-quart baking dish, arrange the chops, potatoes and mushrooms.
In a small bowl combine water, Lipton onion soup mix and pour over the meat.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover the baking dish with foil and bake 1 1/4 hours, or until potatoes are tender.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight jar.
Serve by the teaspoonful in cup of hot water.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together; serve at room temperature.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cut buttered bread in small pieces about 1-inch square.
Place on bottom of casserole dish.
Then place a layer of shrimp and cheese; repeat until all used.
Add soup diluted with 1 can water or milk and eggs.
Pour mixture over bread, shrimp and cheese. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on box.
Pour brownie batter on a 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set. Cool.

title: baker's frosting
directions: Combine milk and flour in saucepan.
Cook until thick and comes away from sides of pan.
Let cool.
Mix sugar, butter, Crisco and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Mix until sugar is not gritty.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until yellow.
Add zucchini; cook and stir 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Either reduce heat and cook until tender, about 25 minutes or put in casserole dish, sprinkle with grated cheese and bake in 375° oven until browned, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This may be prepared the day before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until peanuts quit popping.
Add soda; stir well and pour on greased cookie sheet.
Will break into pieces when cool.

title: chocolate bark
directions: Melt chocolate in the top of a double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square cake pan.
Cool until firm; cut into squares.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soy sauce and lemon juice and pour over greens.
Add noodles at the last minute.

title: sausage balls
directions: Sausage should be at room temperature.
Mix first 3 ingredients, then add biscuit mix.
Blend well.
Roll out in small size balls.
Bake at 350° until brown or 30 minutes.

title: italian style chili
directions: In a frypan, brown meat and onion.
Drain off fat.
In large pot or Dutch oven, add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: elephant ears
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients, except cinnamon and sugar, and mix well.
Divide dough into 12 pieces. Let sit for 10 minutes, then roll out on a lightly floured board. Using hands, stretch each piece in a circle.
Heat vegetable in a 10-inch skillet (cast-iron is preferred).
Place each circle of dough in hot oil and turn once.
The surface will bubble and blister and should be lightly browned.
Turn with spatula and bread knife and place on an absorbent paper towel.
Sprinkle immediately with sugar and cinnamon.

title: mellowscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, and salt in top of double boiler.
Boil over medium heat to a thick syrup (5 minutes).
Mix 1/2 cup milk and cornstarch to a thin paste.
Add 1 3/4 cups milk, combine with hot syrup and cook over hot water until thick and smooth.
Continue to cook 15 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Stir small amount in beaten egg yolks, add to mixture, and cook a few minutes longer. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add butter and mix well.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: minestrone alla calabrese
directions: Mince first 5 ingredients; heat oil in soup pot.
Add ingredients and saute over medium heat until golden.
Add hot water and salt; bring to a boil.
Chop summer vegetables into pieces no bigger than 1/2 inch.
Add all when soup pot reaches a boil and simmer for about 15 minutes.
If too thick, add a cup of hot water.
Core yellow pepper and cut into long, thin strips. Add to simmering soup.
When carrots are tender, add rice and boil gently another 15 minutes or until rice is done.
Serve with cheese.

title: agnes' pumpkin chiffon dessert(diet)
directions: Mix together 2 packages of gelatin and 1/4 cup cold water; set aside.
Beat egg yolks, whipping cream, water, spices and pumpkin. Cook over low heat until hot; add gelatin water and Equal.
Mix well and cool in refrigerator.
Beat egg whites with 1 package of Equal until very stiff; fold into cooled pumpkin mixture.
Add Cool Whip, stirring until well mixed.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on bottom of buttered pan.
Pour in pumpkin mixture and chill.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Note: Only use wooden utensils and non-metallic bowls. Do not refrigerate the starter and do not cover it. Do not make the bread on the day you feed it.

title: chicken with mustard cream
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness and season with salt and pepper.
Spread both sides of chicken with 2 tablespoons mustard and coat with flour.
Melt the butter in a 10-inch skillet over moderately high heat.
Brown the chicken in the butter. Remove chicken to a warm platter.
Pour the cream into skillet and boil rapidly, about 2 minutes, scraping brown bits stuck to the skillet.
Remove skillet from heat and add 1 tablespoon mustard. Add additional mustard and seasoning to taste.
Return chicken to skillet and reheat, basting with sauce.
Serves 4.
Recipe can be halved.

title: out of this world candy
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use small amount of milk until mixture can be made into balls.
Mix well and set into refrigerator to chill. In a double boiler, melt 12 ounce package semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1 cake paraffin.
Roll candy mixture into balls; dip into chocolate mixture.
Use fork or a toothpick to remove and drain on foil.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 7 days.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: chicken country captain
directions: Dress a chicken.
Season inside and out with salt and pepper. Prepare stuffing.
Fill chicken, packing lightly.
Sew up opening. Place in roaster.
Do not cover.
Cook in moderate oven at 300° to 350° until tender.
Allow 25 minutes per pound.
If desired cover breast of chicken with thin strips of salt pork.
Baste frequently.

title: hash brown au gratin potatoes
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put frozen hash browns evenly in dish and salt and pepper to taste.

title: apricot salad
directions: Strain the fruit and save juice.
Mix boiling water with jello until dissolved, then add 1 1/4 cups juice. Cool.
Scald milk and stir in marshmallows until melted. Cool.
Add fruit that you've mashed to jello and milk mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill overnight.

title: barbecue chuck roast
directions: Mix ingredients in roasting pan or crock-pot; place roast on top.
Cook 1 hour per pound.
Shred meat with fork before serving.

title: spareribs and rabbit
directions: Wash the rabbit well and place in a large pot covered with water.
Let come to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium low and cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Add the ribs, the seasonings and 3 cups water.
Cover the pot and let come to a boil.
Reduce the heat to medium low; cook until all the meat is tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in oil.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well.
Combine soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Heat until the cheese melts.
Combine all ingredients and pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. More cooked chicken can be added.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs and Wesson oil.
Sift together flour, soda, sugar and cinnamon.
Add flour mix to the egg and oil.
Mix well.
Add the baby food carrots.
Mix and pour into cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: fancy hush puppies
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Stir in onion.
Separate eggs; beat yolks with milk.
Stir egg mixture into dry ingredients.
Beat the egg whites until smooth, not stiff.
Add a light sprinkle of baking powder to the egg whites just before finished beating them.
Fold egg whites into batter until just mixed.
Make into very small balls.
Drop into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve:
Place 1/3 cup mix per cup hot water.

title: carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Chill.
Mix all other ingredients. Add carrots and marinate overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 10-inch baking dish with Pam.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Then add dry soup mix.
In another bowl, mix hash browns and cheese.
Then pour in baking dish.
Pour butter and soup mix over hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: how to make brown sugar out of white sugar
directions: Mix together.
Takes the place of 1 cup brown sugar when baking.

title: christmas cider
directions: Heat to boiling point. Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 15 minutes. Strain and serve warm.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs.
Throw everything in crock-pot.
Ready in about one hour.

title: sherried black bean soup(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Place first 9 ingredients in a stock pot over heat; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 2 hours or until beans are very soft.
When beans are mushy, add spices, thyme and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat and puree in batches in a food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Return puree to stockpot and stir in sherry.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Cook over low heat for about 5 more minutes or until heated through.
Serve immediately and garnish with egg white and lemon slice.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine garlic and vegetable oil in a small mixing bowl. Cover and let stand several hours.

title: creamed chicken and noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chicken breasts and oil); heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Remove skin and bones while chicken breasts are partially frozen (easier to hand).
Cut meat into cube pieces; allow to completely thaw and drain.
Cook in hot cast-iron skillet with vegetable oil (enough to cover bottom of skillet), stirring meat constantly
until meat is done. Season with salt and pepper while frying.
Allow oil to drain before adding meat to sauce.
Only put enough chicken in skillet to cover bottom each time.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix flour and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: friendly dog salad
directions: Wash lettuce.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Place on salad plate.
Lift one pear half, one prune, 2 orange segments and 1 cherry from containers.
Place on paper towel to dry.
Place pear half, cut side down, on leaf.
Cut prune lengthwise.
Remove pit. Place one prune half at large end of pear half for the ear.
Scoop out tiny hole in pear; place in the raisins for the eye.
Cut cherry in half.
Place 1 piece at narrow end of pear for nose. Use orange segments for collar.
Continue until you use all ingredients.
Fun to make with children.

title: crumb coated cod
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine oil, water and salad dressing mix. Place the stuffing mix in another bowl. Dip fillets in salad dressing mixture, then in stuffing. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: bourbon apples
directions: In a quart casserole, stir together all the ingredients.
They will not fill the baking dish.
Bake covered in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: yam-stuffed sausage
directions: Cut sausage into 3-inch pieces.
Cover with water and cook until tender; drain.
Slice lengthwise to form a pocket.
Arrange on cookie sheet, pocket side up.
Drain yams and pineapple (reserve 3 tablespoons juice).
Mash potatoes and pineapple.
Add sugar, spices and juice; cream well.
Spoon filling into sausage pockets. Dot with butter.

title: peanut butter burst cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until creamy (3 to 5 minutes).
Add egg.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in peanut butter morsels.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix and boil all ingredients (except berries) until thick, about 5 minutes.
Place berries into baked, cooled pie shell. After boiled mixture has cooled, pour over berries.
Place in refrigerator.
Add Cool Whip when ready to serve.
Makes 1 pie.

title: hot mushrooms
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic, salt, mushrooms and parsley.
Saute, stirring until mushrooms are cooked.
Stir in flour, then sour cream.
Blend well (thicken).
Pour into chafing dish.
Grind pepper over.
Serve with Melba toast or toast points.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except water.
Mold in 2 loaf pans. Remove from pans.
Place in 7 x 11 greased baking dish.
Add water.
Bake at 350° about one hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bacon sticks
directions: Wrap bacon around bread sticks that have been dipped into cheese.
Roll again in cheese.
Bake at 350° until crispy.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Add seasoning, tomato paste, soup and water.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine ingredients; beat well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: angel goodies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate together.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle coconut on large piece of waxed paper. Divide mixture in 2 parts.
Put 1/2 on coconut covered paper. Shape into long roll with coconut on outside.
Do the same with other half.
Chill in refrigerator overnight before slicing.

title: baked denver sandwiches
directions: *If adding broccoli, mushrooms or other foods, cut milk to 3 cups.

title: emily's earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix 1st two ingredients in bottom of pan.
Then mix the German chocolate cake mix as directed. Pour over nuts and coconut.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour in greased pie pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Pie will be slightly brown on top.
Serve hot like a quiche.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount of butter.
Mix mushroom soup, milk and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix bread cubes with melted butter.
Add to mixture.
Put layer of carrots, then part of mixture, another layer of carrots and rest of mixture.
Top with 6 strips of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: little pizza loaves
directions: Divide tomato sauce in half.
Mix all ingredients together, reserving half of sauce and the cheese cubes.
Shape into small loaves and place in greased baking pan.
Push cheese cubes into each loaf.
Pour sauce over loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: divine divinity
directions: In saucepan, boil sugar, water, salt and syrup until it forms a hard ball.
Gradually add to beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until stiff enough to spoon out on waxed paper.

title: chocolate chip cookies(yields 10 dozen cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and sugars on medium speed for 5 minutes. Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture and beat until light and fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add on low speed to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix until blended.

title: sponge candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large kettle.
Cook, stirring while sugar melts.
Cook until 300° on candy thermometer or very brittle in cold water.
Remove from heat and add baking soda. Stir gently.
Pour quickly in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool completely and break in pieces.
Dip pieces in melted chocolate and set on wax paper to cool.
This candy tastes just like candy at Christmas called angel candy.

title: freda's seafood salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts, cool down and cut bite size. Add chopped celery, parsley, chives and lemon juice. Cut crab meat to bite size and add to bowl. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise, enough to
moisten. Toss lightly.
Sprinkle dash of paprika on top. Chill and serve. Serves 6.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Drain zucchini well and put in a large bowl.
Add onions, flour, water, oil, eggs and chicken stock (broth), and stir well to make a mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste and stir more.
Oil baking pan and pour contents in.
Preheat oven to 350° 15 minutes prior to baking.
Bake pie for 1 hour or until brown and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Let boil for 1 minute, then add the rest of the ingredients. Spoon out on wax paper.

title: play dough
directions: Mix in order listed.
Cook in saucepan over medium heat until it forms a ball.
Store in covered container and have loads of fun with your children or grandchildren.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn.
Combine in saucepan the brown sugar, corn syrup and margarine.
Cook over low heat to hard ball; remove from heat.
Add 1 can of sweetened condensed milk.
Pour over popcorn; stir to coat.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Mix pancake batter.
Pour into 3 to 4-inch pancakes.
Cut thin pieces of banana, placing several pieces in pancake before flipping.
Serve with maple syrup.
Great.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets and boil until cooked, then peel them, slice them and put them in the syrup mixture.
Bring to a boil; pack in jars and seal while hot.

title: italian gravy
directions: In large pot heat olive oil.
Add pork bones until lightly browned.
Add 1/2 clove garlic, then add puree and water.
Put in crushed tomatoes and put in some Parmesan cheese.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and 6 basil leaves.
Put in some more garlic.
Bring to boil, then turn down heat to low.
Cook about 2 or 3 hours. Stir well every so often.
Serve with favorite pasta and garlic bread.
Enjoy.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt chocolates in double boiler, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat.
Mix in peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Spread mixture in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill pan in refrigerator until mixture is firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl, saving dressing for last. Pour dressing over caviar and let sit for 1 hour. Drain excess dressing and serve. Good with corn chips.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix onion, cheese, soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and parsley together well.
Add potatoes and pour into a 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas strawberry pie
directions: Sieve 2 cups of berries using both pulp and juice.
Mix flour and sugar; add to sieved strawberries.
Cook for 10 minutes; cool. Dissolve gelatin; mix with strawberry mixture.
Mix cream and cream cheese; spread in pie shell.
Line pie shell with remaining whole berries.
Pour cooled strawberry mixture over top.
Chill. Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamy noodle supper
directions: You may substitute the cream of chicken soup for cream of mushroom soup, tuna (7 ounce can) for the chicken and peas for the green beans for a different taste.

title: butter shortbread
directions: Cream butter and shortening thoroughly; gradually add sifted flour and cornstarch.
Mix until flour is moistened.
Spread on cookie sheet; refrigerate overnight.
Bake starting at 300° for 1 hour.
Optional:
Chop up 2 large Cadbury milk chocolate bars and sprinkle over hot cookies.
Spread when melted.
Cut while warm.

title: holiday dilly bread
directions: Soak yeast in lukewarm water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
Add sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast mixture.
Add flour to make a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Knead, then cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down; turn into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart round 8-inch casserole dish and let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or slightly more.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, milk, lard and nuts. Spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Mix the brown sugar and cocoa; spread on top.
Pour hot water evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mash bananas with fork.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into buttered loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: In medium pan bring water, rice and salt to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove from heat and stir in milk, vanilla and raisins.
Return to heat and quickly stir in eggs.
Stir constantly over low heat until pudding coats metal spoon.
Pour into serving dish and sprinkle with nutmeg. Serve warm or cold.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream together butter, oil and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour and cream of tartar into a large bowl.
Add creamed mixture to dry ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet. Press down with fork or bottom of a glass.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until nicely browned.
(You may want to use only 1/4 the amount of ingredients.)

title: strawberry punch
directions: Beat strawberries until smooth.
Add grape juice.
Add soda just before using.

title: rye rounds
directions: Grate carrots, cheese and onions; add salt, pepper and milk to soften.
Mix together until it forms a sort of paste.
Let stand for a while until flavors blend (at least 1 hour).
To serve, spread mixture on rye rounds (party rye) and toast.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli with cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add all ingredients, except cheese and cracker crumbs.
In a 2-quart casserole, alternate mixture, cheese and crumbs.
Finish with crumbs on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, covered with foil, or until bubbly.
Remove foil and brown crumbs.

title: cookie icing
directions: Combine egg white and honey in a bowl. Gradually add sugar, beating well. Dip or spread on cookies.
Lay one layer at a time to harden.
"Very tasty."

title: baked caramel apples
directions: Cut apples in half and remove cores.
Place 1 dot butter and 1 caramel in apple.
Butter a small baking dish.
Add apples and 1/2 inch water.
Bake 15 minutes at 475°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Blanch broccoli.
Drain broccoli and line the outer sides of a 9 x 13 inch glass dish leaving it hollow in the center.
Shred chicken and fill the hollow cavity in the middle of the broccoli.
Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise, curry powder and cheese.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Crush or crumble stuffing mix and put evenly over entire casserole.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: chess pie no. 2
directions: Melt butter and mix ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for
40 to 50 minutes in an unbaked pie shell.
Yield:
2 large pies or 3 small pies.

title: quick refrigerator pickles
directions: *This recipe divided into half works well also.

title: squash casserole(from gertrude hart's recipe file)
directions: Add butter, salt, pepper, onion, milk, cheese and crackers to squash.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix and put into pie shell (mix just with spoon).
Put into pie shell and chill.
Makes about 1 1/2 pies.
Double makes 3 pies.

title: ruby's pie crust
directions: Mix well and roll out.
Double for 2 crusts.

title: microwave mints
directions: Put butter and milk in 2-quart bowl. Cook on High 45 seconds or until melted. Stir in frosting mix. Cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until bubbly. Stir twice. Stir in food coloring to tint.
Add extract. Drop mixture by teaspoon onto wax paper. When cool, store in airtight container.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Squeeze shrimp, scallions and celery very well to get water and juice out. Mix all ingredients together. Serve on a bed of lettuce with soup or on a sandwich.

title: amazing egg custard pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla. Beat with mixer 3 minutes.
Pour in 9-inch pie pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup cooking oil, 1 cup warm water and eggs and beat 2 minutes.
Add pudding and beat 1 minute.
Fold in poppy seed.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves or 1 Bundt pan.
Best if frozen several days.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown meat in oil in large pot. Remove meat and saute vegetables.

Add seasoning, Worcestershire sauce, broth and tomato sauce; simmer 15 minutes. Add meat and rice; stir. Cover and cook 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook 20 minutes more over low heat. Serves 8.

title: chicken spaghetti dinner
directions: Heat pepper and onion in butter.
Add spaghetti to chicken broth and cook until tender.
Combine all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: cookies for diabetics
directions: Boil the first 6 ingredients together for 3 minutes; cool. Add the beaten eggs, soda, salt and artificial sweetener.
Add the flour and baking powder.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chunky chili
directions: Coat a medium saucepan with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and green pepper; saute 1 minute.
Add jalapeno pepper and garlic.
Saute an additional 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add ground turkey; cook 5 minutes or until turkey is browned, stirring frequently.
Add chopped tomatoes and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: snack wieners
directions: Cut wieners into 1-inch lengths.
Mix all other ingredients and add wieners.
Cook in crock-pot for several hours on low heat.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples; mix with sugar, salt, cinnamon and lemon juice. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter; put pie top on top and crimp around edge with floured fork or fingers and thumb.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, bring sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pie plate.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter, the cream cheese and sugar well.
Add vanilla. Slowly add flour.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: scones
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients, then add buttermilk and soda.
Sift and add flour, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Roll out and cut.
Bake on low heated griddle on top of the stove.
Brown on each side and cool.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Drain oranges into saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and sugar; add to juice in pan.
Bring to boiling point; cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add Jell-O; stir well.
Cool slightly and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep Pyrex dish; set aside. Mix sugar, flour and salt; add milk. Pour over melted butter. Do not stir. Pour peaches and juice over flour mixture. Do not stir. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to cream mixture alternately with banana, blending well after each addition. Stir in nuts. Pour into well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until well done. Remove; cool on rack. Wrap and store overnight.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Mix mayo and sugar.
Gradually add vinegar.
Add sliced cucumbers and onions.
Store in refrigerator.

title: liptauer cheese dip
directions: Prepare day before using.

title: delicious apricot cake
directions: Combine.
Bake in a tube pan for 60 minutes at 325°.
Turn out immediately and, while still hot, glaze with:

title: meat loaf(easy)
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven and spread additional ketchup on the top and then bake for another 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Add sugar to cream cheese.
Blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time and blend.
Add vanilla.
Measure 2 cups cheese mixture and fold into melted, cooled chocolate.
Add lemon juice to remaining cheese mixture.
Pour into well-buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Top with chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool, then chill.

title: orange-cream bagel spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: german chocolate caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/2 cup of evaporated milk in double boiler.
In mixing bowl, combine rest of milk, butter, and cake mix.
Take 1/2 of cake mix and spread on bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Press out with hands.
Bake for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of cake.
Spread melted caramels on top of chips.
Crumble the rest of the cake mix on top.
Bake for 16-18 minutes.

title: homemade payday candy bars
directions: Layer the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or jellyroll pan with 1 jar of nuts. In a medium saucepan, melt oleo and marshmallows. Add the condensed milk and peanut butter chips. Stir until melted. Evenly pour over layered nuts. Top with the second jar of peanuts. Press with fingers. Let set until firm. Cut into squares and serve.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in non-stick skillet, add flour, stir and cook 1 minute (until pasty on low heat).
Add shredded cheese, cook until melted; remove from heat and set aside.
Drain cooked beans and put in baking dish (9 x 13), pour cheese mixture over top.
Crush 1/2 package Ritz crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Spread on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 100% parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in margarine.
Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Slice, arrange and pat cookie dough on foil lined pizza pan to form 1 large cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Arrange fresh fruits on cooled cookie sheet.
Glaze with a mixture of orange marmalade and water.
Bananas should be treated with lemon juice to preserve freshness and prevent discoloring.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Brown sausage in saucepan or skillet. Add celery, mushrooms and onions; cook 3 minutes.
Add broth and seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes about 5 cups stuffing or 10 servings.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Mix all together until mixed well.
Knead until smooth; work with hands.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Bake on low heat until light brown.
Serves 36.

title: fabulous cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: southern-style baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, add shortening and blend together until corn meal consistency.
Pour milk into flour mixture and add egg.
Stir to stiff dough.
Knead 5 minutes.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown onion, pepper and hamburger.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in a casserole dish.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: Cook and mash potatoes, adding milk to them.
Steam cabbage. Drain and chop fine.
Combine potato mixture and cabbage.
Season to taste.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine corn syrup and brown sugar; cook until it boils.
Stir in condensed milk; stir until it comes to a second boil.
Add butter; cook for another 3 minutes.
Pour over popcorn; stir until all is coated.
Shape into balls.

title: easy beef enchiladas
directions: Combine ground beef and onions; brown in a skillet.
When browned, drain off grease and return to skillet.
Add 3 cups Cheddar cheese and stir.
Mixture will stick together.
Warm tortillas in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes until flexible.
Fill and roll each enchilada with 2 tablespoons of meat mixture.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese, whipping cream and sugar.
Add all other ingredients and pack in mold that has been lightly sprayed with Pam; cover tightly and freeze until ready to serve.
Slice thin and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: Combine chicken and cornstarch in small bowl.
Toss to coat.

title: linda's dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: fried broccoli(delicious)
directions: Chop and slice broccoli and stems fairly thin.
Saute garlic in oil.
Stir-fry broccoli in garlic and oil.
When almost tender, sprinkle Parmesan cheese over while still stirring with fork. Cook 2 more minutes and serve.

title: marble cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add milk and mix well.
Prepare flour and sift together with baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture and mix until smooth.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa, then add salt, vanilla, peanut butter and oats until it loses its shine.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
They will set up while cooling.

title: mrs. reese's divinity candy
directions: Boil until it threads.

title: s.o.s. sausage casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spread over bread and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk and thyme; add pepper.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken with rice
directions: In a large 2-quart casserole, combine the rice and soup. Place chicken on top of mixture; sprinkle with dry onion soup mix. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
You can uncover for the last 15 minutes, until slightly browned.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs;
add sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and syrup and stir.
Add	nuts,
vanilla	and melted butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.	Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pan or 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Mix all ingredients in medium sized bowl. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Pour into pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: chicken curry
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pat chicken with paper towels.
Combine flour and pepper and sprinkle over both sides of chicken breasts. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Saute chicken 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from skillet with a wide cake turner and place in a large heat-proof casserole. Saute onion, garlic, green pepper, curry powder and thyme.
Saute in skillet 5 minutes until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes.
Stir until heated through.
Pour tomato mixture over chicken casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes until tender.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook pepper in butter or margarine until tender. Add soup, milk, chicken and pimiento.
Heat, stirring occasionally. Spoon into shells.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Pour into a 1-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl and sprinkle over top.
Bake until golden, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sarah's honey-broiled scallops
directions: Rinse scallops.
In a mixing bowl, combine lime juice, oil, honey, soy sauce and ginger.
Add scallops and mix until well coated.
Cover and chill 3 to 6 hours, stirring frequently. Remove scallops from marinade, reserving marinade.

title: short ribs
directions: Dust short ribs in flour and pepper (no salt).
Brown short ribs and garlic in small amount of oil in Dutch oven.
Drain. Mix soy sauce, honey and water.
Pour over ribs and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: another never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Add salt, egg, water and vinegar.
Form into a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until cold.
Will keep for 2 to 3 weeks if kept in airtight container.

title: grandpa's favorite dressing(grandpa simpson)
directions: Mix mayonnaise, catsup and milk until smooth.
Add more milk or catsup if too thick.
Finely chop egg and pickle if used.
Use salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Serve on green salad. Keeps several days in the refrigerator.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix onion and water.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add dried beef which has been snipped. Refrigerate before serving. Good with crackers.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Pour over popped corn (do not salt corn).
Put butter on hands before making balls.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix together sifted flour with remaining ingredients.
Place in two small greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush Oreos with butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save a little bit of the Oreos.
Combine pudding and milk.
Mix until thick.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add in pudding mix. Add in Cool Whip.

title: soft ginger bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Then add boiling water.
Pour into a small square pan or a loaf pan and bake at 325° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: christmas jello delight
directions: Mix lime Jello according to directions and allow to set.
Mix lemon Jello, cream cheese and pineapple. Place on jelled lime Jello and allow to set.
Mix strawberry Jello and place on previous Jello and allow to set.
Use about 9 inch square bowl. Garnish with mint or holly.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: upside-down pumpkin torte
directions: Beat the first 9 ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Take 1/2 stick oleo and the yellow cake mix.
Cut the two together and sprinkle over the top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Test with toothpick.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large ovenproof skillet, brown chops in oil.
Remove from skillet; pour off fat in skillet.
Combine lemon juice and cornstarch; mix well.
Add sugar, onion, soy sauce, bouillon and reserved syrup.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened and bouillon is dissolved.
Add pork chops and carrots; cover.
Bake 1 hour or until tender.
Add pineapple; cover and bake 10 minutes.
Garnish with green peppers.
Serve with rice if desired.

title: chicken in a blanket
directions: Boil chicken breasts, celery and onion until tender with enough water to cover.
Remove from broth.
Reserve 1 1/4 cups broth.
Cool chicken slightly.
Separate crescent dough and cut chicken into 8 pieces.
Roll crescent dough around chicken and place in buttered casserole dish (about 9 x 13-inch) so they don't touch (do not stack).
Mix cream of chicken soup with broth. Pour over chicken rolls.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: pone bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make small pones and pat out flat. Place in well-greased (Crisco oil) pan.
Bake at 350° to 400° until brown.
Serve with beans, peas, greens, etc.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Mix tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat.
Add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Mix well.
Put in ungreased dish.
Bake in 400° oven 20 minutes. Makes two dishes.

title: jiffy peach cobbler
directions: Drain and save juice from fruit.
Melt margarine in a large baking dish.
Add flour, sugar, milk and drained fruit to dish. Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour fruit juice over cobbler.
Return to oven and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Suitable for freezing.

title: chicken madrid(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken pieces and brown on both sides.
Remove chicken from skillet and reserve.
Add onion, green and red bell peppers and garlic to skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until onion slices are transparent.
Return reserved chicken to skillet.
Add tomatoes with their liquid.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer, covered 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Top with basil and serve at once.
Quick and easy.
Makes plain chicken great.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Mix together vinegar, sugar, salt, mayonnaise and Green Goddess dressing.
Mix in vegetables. Refrigerate.
Better if made one day ahead.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Heat oil, vinegar, and sugar until sugar melts. Pour over vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onions and pepper in oleo.
Crumble cold cornbread; add to onion and pepper.
Add milk, sage and black pepper.
Mix well. Add soup and mix again.
Add squash.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 450° until brown.
This freezes well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix by hand to blend.
Drop into
balls about the size of a walnut on two cookie sheets.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and boil in salt water until soft.

title: no-cook divinity
directions: Mix frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and water in a small mixer bowl.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to larger mixer bowl.
Gradually blend in powdered sugar on low speed.
Stir nuts and drop onto waxed paper.
Let outside firm and turn over.
Allow to dry for 12 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash, drain and de-stem mushrooms.
Mix cheese, bacon and onion.
Stuff mushrooms with cheese mixture.
Put on broiling pan. You may broil, bake, grill or saute in butter.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: frozen cucumber slices
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain and add vinegar and sugar; mix well.
Pack into containers and freeze.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples and place in greased baking dish. Sift in bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir in egg. Spread over apples and drizzle with butter. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Serve with ice cream.

title: mimi's cheese crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small rounds. Flatten and prick with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion together and drain.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Layer tortillas and meat alternately.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In large casserole dish, dice butter and place in bottom of dish.
Add cracker crumbs.
Add a layer of green beans, cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, onions and cheese.
Add cracker crumbs and bacon bits on top.
Cook for 30 minutes at 300°.
If any is left over the next day, just add a can of cream of mushroom soup and water and heat.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix in order given; beat well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350°.
When cool, frost.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan, or spray with Pam. Take bone and skin off the chicken.
Break up chicken into pieces in casserole.
Add 2 cans cream of celery soup and chicken broth, mixed well.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour and sweet milk.
Add melted butter and spoon over chicken.
Cook at 400° for 1 hour or until crust is brown.

title: cucumber cubes
directions: Put cucumber cubes and salt in gallon jar or crock; pour 1/2 gallon of boiling water over cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 1 week; stir every day with a wooden or plastic spoon.
Drain and add alum and the other 1/2 gallon of boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and make syrup.
Place mustard seed and spices in a cloth or spice ball.
Boil sugar, vinegar and spices and pour over cucumbers in gallon jar.
Reheat syrup every day for 4 days and pour back over cucumber cubes.
On the fifth day, pack cucumbers in pint jars.
Heat syrup and pour over cubes in pint jars.
Seal and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: honey and mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: mom's mock turkey
directions: Mix well in buttered baking dish.
Bake in slow oven about 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken delight
directions: Arrange in layers vegetable, chicken, 2 soups (mixed together).
Make stuffing according to directions and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown on top.

title: corn flake candy
directions: In medium saucepan, combine syrup and brown sugar.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in cereal.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
These can be put into spaghetti sauce or frozen.
Serves 6.
(Freezes well.)

title: darlene's delight
directions: Mix all ingredients well!
Chill for at least one hour.

title: wrapped chicken breast supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Grease bottom of casserole and line with chipped beef. Place chicken breasts on top of beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered in 275° oven for 3 hours.

title: tomato-cucumber marinade
directions: Marinate 5 to 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour, a little at a time, until all used up.
Add nuts and stir in potato chips very gently.
Make in small balls.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 16 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle both sides of pork chops with salt.
Place pork in ungreased shallow baking pan.
Top each with onion slice, lemon slice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon ketchup.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, spooning sauce onto pork occasionally until done.
Yields 4 servings, 410 calories per serving.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve hard-cooked eggs lengthwise; remove yolks and mash.
Mix other ingredients.
Refill whites.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces and put into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Fix jello as directed on box.
Pour over cake pieces. Put in refrigerator to set.
After jello is set, put Cool Whip on top and store in refrigerator.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown beef, hot dogs, bacon and onion.
Drain.
Add brown sugar, white sugar, mustard, vinegar, salt and ketchup.
Stir in and place in casserole dish or pan.
Add 3 kinds of beans.
Do not drain.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery together.
Remove, drain and cool.

title: aunt reva's apple raisin cake
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a pan; bring to a boil and set aside.
In a big mixing bowl, put enough apples to make a pie, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix both batches of ingredients together.
Bake in a broiler pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost while warm with dark chocolate frosting.
Very moist and yummy.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli
to
3 minutes.
Pour in bowl and beat until fine; add all other ingredients.
Continue beating until smooth. Bake
in buttered casserole for 45 minutes to an hour at 350° in pan of water.

title: cilantro chicken
directions: Spread oil in skillet.
Clean chicken and season.
Place in skillet on low heat.
Cover with onions, cilantro, garlic and chile and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until done next to bone.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Mix well and refreeze.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer at medium speed.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar.
Add milk to make a thin batter.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Add blackberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Make 1-inch diameter meat balls and brown in skillet.
After browning, put meat balls in crock-pot with 2 cans of soup and simmer for several hours. Excellent party dish.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat cider, cloves, allspice, cinnamon and sugar to boiling. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain punch and pour in punch bowl. Float oranges in bowl.
A great holiday favorite.

title: linda's pork chops
directions: Flour pork chops and fry in butter with finely chopped onions. Sprinkle chops with garlic salt and pepper.
Add 1 can beef consomme and 1 can sliced peaches (drained) and cover.
Simmer for 1 hour or longer.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: duchess soup
directions: Saute potatoes, celery and onion in butter.
Add mixed vegetables.
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Add chicken base and chicken.
Add cheese and milk.
Bring to boil, then add flour and water paste to thicken or if you have leftover mashed potatoes, add it to thicken, instead of flour.
Cook slow until thick.
Serve with hot rolls or bread.

title: icing in the cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, water and icing.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add oil and mix well.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour in Bundt pan.
To test, insert toothpick into cake. Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Work together cheese and flour. Add margarine.
Mix well with fork.
Mold 1 teaspoon mix around each olive.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
(Can be frozen.)
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Make dressing mixture according to package directions.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Line tray with wax paper.
In medium microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips, vanilla milk chips and shortening.
Microwave on High 1 minute.
Stir.
Microwave 15 seconds, stir, then an additional 30 seconds, until chips are melted when stirred. Holding top, dip bottom 2/3 of each strawberry into melted mixture; shake gently to remove excess.
Place on prepared tray. Refrigerate about 1 hour or until coating is firm.
For best results, use within 24 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to box directions. Spread half of the batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Melt caramels with butter and milk.
Spread on cake and sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips. Spread remaining batter on top. Bake 20 minutes more at 375°.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, powdered milk, salt and sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Mix in egg and vegetables.
Add enough water so that mixture forms a ball.
Pat out dough 1/2 inch thick with your fingers on a lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Cut with your favorite cookie cutter, such as a small, heart-shaped one, or use a doggie biscuit cutter.
Pat out all scraps.
Proceed as above.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on cake rack.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Form into small balls (1-inch).
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over very low heat. Dip candy balls into chocolate.
Cool on wax paper.

title: easy make cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not mix ingredients.
Empty pineapple in pan and spread evenly.
Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherry pie filling. Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Cut margarine into slices and space evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine milk and the 1 cup of water.
Scald.
Pour scalded liquid over shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir until melted.
When lukewarm, add 2 cups of flour. Add softened yeast, then oats.
Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and satiny, about 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl and brush top with melted shortening.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Brush with melted shortening.
Let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: bran buttermilk muffins
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and egg until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; stir in bran cereal.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir just until combined.
Bake in a 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Ritz.
Fill individual shells or bakers with mixture.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: lemon sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add half and half and vanilla; blend in sour cream (mixture will appear slightly curdled).
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Pour into 3 cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours. Unmold and serve with fruit.
Makes 2 1/2 cups or 5 servings.

title: corn bread deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in a well-greased pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: spring onion soup
directions: Heat 1 cup broth and pour over mushrooms in small bowl.
Soak mushrooms 30 minutes; strain and reserve liquid.
Finely mince mushrooms.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice to boiling. Add jello and cool. Add buttermilk, nuts and Cool Whip. Mix well and chill until set.

title: quick and easy chicken and noodles
directions: Combine all together and cook until noodles are done (about 20 minutes).
May serve as main dish or with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: broccoli pecan casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add soup, mayo and chopped pecans.
Mix well. Add eggs and onion. Pour into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine the shortening and onion; brown.
Add the remaining ingredients; simmer for 20 minutes.
(You may add water to the mixture as desired.)

title: ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In medium saucepan, heat cheese and cream, stirring constantly, until cheese melts and sauce is creamy. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly; bake 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cookie cutter sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt, and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Mix.
Divide dough.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375 degrees.
For the icing, blend confectioners sugar, water and food coloring. Ice cookies when cool.

title: sour cream salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Place in loaf pan, lightly greased, and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place nuts in shallow baking pan. Combine ingredients and pour over nuts, stirring well.
Bake 20 minutes, stirring several times.
Cool on paper towels and store in airtight jars.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and syrup.
(In that order.)
If margarine hasn't cooled, eggs will begin to cook. Divide evenly into each shell, the nuts and chocolate chips. Pour mixture into shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: icy fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine Cool Whip, mayonnaise, cream cheese and sugar. Blend thoroughly. Fold in the remaining ingredients. Chill at least 2 hours before serving. Serve on a bed of lettuce with a tea biscuit (or some other salty cookie).

title: mors grov brod(brown bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water; let stand 15 minutes.
Add 3 1/2 cups lukewarm water, molasses, salt, sugar and shortening. Add enough flour to make a soft sponge.
Beat thoroughly for about 10 minutes, then add rest of flour to make stiff dough.
Knead, then place in greased bowl, cover and set in warm place.
When doubled in bulk, knead again.
Let rise once more, then shape into loaves.
Let rise until light, then bake about 45 minutes in moderate oven.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Makes 4 medium loaves.
Try adding chopped walnuts to part of the dough for a delicious nut bread.

title: caramel layer bars
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, brown sugar and oats.
Cut in butter until particles are fine.
Reserve 2 cups.
Press in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine flour and caramel sauce.
Spread over oatmeal base.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, then crumble reserved crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: old-fashioned beans
directions: Place beans in	bean
pot
with
water; onion, salt and salt pork.
Cook overnight.
Add remaining ingredients, cook 1 to 2 hours longer.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sauce and pour over vegetables.
