Cover and chill at least 3 hours before serving (preferably overnight).
I store in Ziploc bag and turn often.
Keeps 1 week.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Pour all ingredients in blender; blend well. Batter will be thin. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs and half and half.
Scramble in butter in large skillet.
Put scrambled eggs in a 3-quart shallow casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour on soup, mushrooms and cheese.
Top with bacon. Bake at 250° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Can be halved or doubled and can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated.
Then bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot-zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger lightly.
Layer in cake pan 1/2 of carrots and 1/2 of zucchini.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Layer hamburger, soup and taco mix.
Top with zucchini, carrots and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Combine orange juice, rind and egg; pour all at once in dry ingredients. Mix until all flour is dampened. Add cranberries and nuts.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Spread corners and sides slightly higher than middle.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until toothpick comes clear and crust is brown. Store overnight.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake a 10 inch skillet of cornbread. Let cool and crumble up in large bowl. Add chopped onion, green pepper (chopped), tomatoes (chopped) and crumbled bacon. Mix well and add mayonnaise. Serve with cooked dried beans.

title: szechwan chicken with cashews
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2 inch pieces.
Mix egg white, 1 tsp cornstarch, 1 tsp salt, ginger, 1 tsp soy sauce and black pepper in a big glass bowl.
Stir in chicken, cover and refrigerate at least for 1 hour.
Heat 1 Tbsp oil in a 10-inch skillet until hot. Stir-fry cashew until light brown about 1 minute.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with 1/2 tsp salt.
Heat 2 Tbsp oil until hot. Add chicken, stir-fry about 1 minute.
Add chicken, chicken broth, and reserved mushroom liquid.
Heat to boiling.
Mix 1 Tbsp cornstarch, 1 Tbsp water and 1 Tbsp soy sauce.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 1 minute.
Stir in cashew nuts, and garnish with reserved green onion tops.
Serve over white rice.

title: aji de gallina peru(spicy, hot chicken)
directions: Soak bread crumbs in chicken broth.
Fry onion, garlic, paprika, hot pepper and cumin seed together in some margarine. Then add bread soaked in chicken broth to the onion mixture.
Add the chicken which has been cut into small pieces and heat through. If sauce appears too thick, add more broth.
Add salt and pepper to taste, even more hot pepper, if desired.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Saute onion for several minutes in margarine.
Cook beef until brown; drain.
Pour onion, margarine and tomato sauce over mixed vegetables.
Simmer several minutes.
Mix cornbread mix as directed.
Pour over top of beef and vegetables and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Place in casserole dish. Combine soup, eggs, cheese, onion and mayonnaise; mix well.
Pour over cooked broccoli.
Crush Ritz crackers; spread over top of mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tofu cheesecake
directions: Have ready 1 granola pie crust.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Place half of the mixture in a blender and whiz until very smooth.
Empty blender into crust.
Repeat with other half.
Smooth out the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Chill thoroughly and serve.
Top with your favorite topping or fresh fruit, if desired.

title: kugelhupp(german cake)
directions: Blend butter, sugar, yolks and lemon juice.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, adding milk slowly.
Into this fold egg whites. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Check to see if cake is done by inserting cake tester.
If no dough adheres, it is.
Turn out immediately.

title: chicken, broccoli and tortellini
directions: Saute chicken until cooked through.
Boil broccoli and tortellini until cooked.
Mix these together.
Mix sauce as directed, and pour over chicken mixture.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cut celery, onion and pepper into small pieces.
Put on top of beef in roaster.
Mix catsup, water, vinegar, salt and pepper. Pour over the beef. Roast about 3 hours if using stewing beef and 4 hours if you use a roast. As soon as tender, shred beef with fork while hot.
Bake at 325°.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Sift together the flour, soda and cinnamon. Add to egg mixture.
Fold in carrots. Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cornmeal pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add milk and egg until fairly smooth. Cook on a hot griddle (375°).
Makes 8.

title: lemon-orange jello
directions: Mix pineapple, mandarin oranges and orange juice.

title: cheezy kielbasa and kraut
directions: Rinse sauerkraut to remove most of the salt content.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch roasting pan.
Slice kielbasa in 1/2-inch slices; arrange on top of sauerkraut.
Top with Swiss cheese slices.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender; drain.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, mix soup and milk.
Drain green beans.
Add and blend together.
Add 1/2 can of fried onions.
Blend.
Put remaining onions on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
For a cup of hot chocolate put 2 tablespoons mix in cup and fill with hot water.

title: blueberry - banana surprise pie
directions: Blend sugar and cream cheese.
Blend this mixture with Cool Whip.
Slice bananas on the bottom of cooked pie crust.
Sprinkle chopped pecans.
Spread Blueberry pie mix, then top with cream cheese - Cool Whip mixture.
Chill.
(Other pie mixes may be substitute in place of blueberry.)

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peaches.
Fold in peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: party chicken
directions: Roll chicken and bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Place in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Spoon over chicken rolls. Bake 3 hours in oven at 275°.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve 1 cake yeast (I use 1 package dry yeast) in lukewarm water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Let rise about 2 hours in warm place.
Work down and make in rolls.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: trader's punch
directions: Mix orange juice, lemon juice and grenadine syrup; pour over ice to chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale (chilled) and fresh fruit in season.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased loaf pan and bake in 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Best if made the day before.

title: fried chicken
directions: Soak chicken in salty water for at least 1 hour.
Put in paper bag and shake to coat.
In skillet, have 1 to 1 1/2 cups Crisco or oil melted and medium hot.
Put pieces in hot fat.
Put lid on top.
Brown on both sides.
Should cook in 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Spread evenly into 9 x 13-inch pan or round pizza pan.
Top with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, grated Cheddar cheese and black sliced olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mandarin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 18 regular muffin cups.
Beat butter and sugar until pale yellow and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Sift all-purpose flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in whole wheat flour.
Add vanilla to orange juice.
Fold flour mixture into butter mixture alternately with orange juice, ending with flour.
Fold in oranges, then nuts.
Spoon into muffin cups and bake until lightly brown, about 30 minutes.

title: stuffed scallops
directions: Butter a casserole.
Wash scallops; pat dry.
Put into a casserole.
Crush crackers until fine.
Add melted butter and herbs; mix.
Sprinkle over scallops.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese and oregano.
Separate rolls.
Spread butter and sprinkle cheese mixture.
Roll up lengthwise around sausages. Slice and bake according to package directions.

title: spinach-strawberry salad
directions: In a blender mix together the sugar, Wor. sauce, olive oil and vinegar.
Then add to the dressing the seeds and blend for a few seconds.
Just before serving, mix dressing with the strawberries and spinach.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook in heavy pan or skillet to 238° on candy thermometer.
Add margarine and Spanish peanuts.
Cook to 325°, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and quickly add baking soda.
Stir as it foams, then spread thin on cookie sheet (buttered).
Be sure to use raw peanuts.

title: german fried vegetables
directions: Toss all vegetables with equal amounts of flour and corn meal. Fry as you would okra, using 1/2 shortening and 1/2 butter.

title: italian beef and rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add salt, tomatoes, water, rice, mushrooms and pepper.
Bring to a full boil over low heat; cover and simmer about 25 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: squash relish
directions: Pour over squash mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Process pints 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: mock sukiyaki
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add vegetables, beef broth and soy sauce. Cover; cook over heat for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Stir often.
Combine water and cornstarch; add to meat mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over hot rice.

title: gazpacho-style shrimp
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water and salt.
Bring to boil. Add shrimp and simmer 1 to 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink; drain.

title: slaw
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover with 1 cup of sugar; do not stir.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain; cool.
Mix McCormick Salad Supreme and salad dressing; add vegetables and spaghetti.
Let sit overnight.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix. Pour over hot crust and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Saute onion, garlic, mushrooms and green pepper.
Add the beans, tomatoes, spices, salt and wine.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Layer tortillas, sauce and 3 tablespoons grated Jack and 3 tablespoons cheese mixture.
Repeat until all used up, ending with layer of sauce.
Garnish with cheese, yogurt and black olives. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: virginia spoon bread
directions: Mix together meal, butter, salt and sugar.
Then pour 1 cup boiling water over the mixture and mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Bake in Pyrex baking dish 1 hour at 350°.

title: crabmeat fondue
directions: Drain crabmeat (if canned); chop if fresh.
Set aside.
Butter a 6 cup straight sided casserole (most important; don't use a bowl).
Layer by thirds the fish, bread and cheese.
Sprinkle between layers the onion and parsley.
Beat together eggs, milk, butter and mustard.
Pour over layers.
Cover; chill overnight (or at least 3 hours).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Warm soup and mix in gelatin until dissolved.
Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Mix with soup and gelatin mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into greased mold. Make the night before.

title: garden marinara sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in medium size pan.
Add onion.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce; heat to boiling.
Add tomato paste; simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sugar, oregano, basil, red pepper, salt, sun-dried tomatoes and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes more and pour over your favorite noodles.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Bring to a boil; add the cucumbers.
Mix and boil slowly for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings in large saucepan until tender. Add beans, ground beef, water, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, brown sugar and molasses; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 40 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine broth, soups, pimento strips, cheese spread, onion and chili powder in a saucepan.
Simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, layer the following: 1/3 of the corn chips, half of the chicken, half of the sauce, 1/3 of the corn chips, instant rice and half of the chicken.
Pour the remaining sauce over this.
Top with the remaining corn chips. Bake uncovered in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: frosted strawberry squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (40 minutes if recipe is doubled).
Stir occasionally while baking. Spread 2/3 of the crumbs in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish; let cool.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion and pepper in hot oil till tender.
Stir in flour. Add rest of ingredients except shrimp and rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: chopped spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with Hawaiian Bread.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish.
Cover casserole and bake 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes, until cheese is bubbly and crusty on edges.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots 10 minutes; drain and set aside.
Bring tomato mixture to boil.
Pour over carrots and set aside.
Chop 1 medium onion and cut up 1 large green pepper.
Add to carrots. Refrigerate overnight.

title: maple fluff dessert
directions: Line loaf cake pan with vanilla wafers and melted oleo.
Cream powdered sugar and 1/2 cup oleo.
Add next three ingredients. Pour over the wafers and freeze.
Whip Dream Whip or use frozen whipped topping and beat in maple pancake syrup.
Add marshmallows and pecans.
Pour over first layer and refreeze.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: date nut ball
directions: Boil dates, sugar and butter until pasty; add Rice Krispies and nuts. Roll into balls, then roll into powdered sugar.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Add chicken, soup, milk and cheese; mix well.
Put in casserole dish and bake 20 minutes, uncovered, in 425° oven.

title: vegetable-vegetarian soup
directions: Thaw vegetables.
Place in a large stockpot all of the ingredients except spaghetti sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook slowly for 30 or 40 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer for another 30 minutes.
You may add any vegetables or leave out any of the vegetables that you choose except tomatoes. This makes about 1 1/2 gallons of soup, rather thick, you may even call it goulash.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish, one-quart size.
Saute bread crumbs, celery and onion in oleo.
Add milk and eggs, then seasoning.
Pour over chicken.
Spread soup over top.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken melba
directions: Coat chicken breasts with flour, paprika, garlic, salt and pepper. In large frying pan, brown chicken quickly in vegetable oil. Place browned chicken in single layer in shallow baking pan. On each chicken breast, layer mushrooms, then cover with Mozzarella cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Make 1 package strawberry jello according to package directions.
Let chill until starting to thicken.
Put layer of strawberries in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and pour jello over the strawberries.
Chill until firm.
Make 1 package jello according to package directions, using a little less water than what it calls for.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat with pint of softened ice cream until mixed well.
Pour on top of strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate until firm before serving.

title: quick breakfast rolls
directions: In saucepan, heat brown sugar, syrup and margarine until margarine is melted and mixture is bubbly.
Pour into a 9-inch round cake pan.
Cover with chopped nuts.
Place biscuits over mixture.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown. Let set about 2 to 3 minutes and turn over onto plate.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients and add to the other items.
Chill. Serve 18 to 20.

title: hot beef stew, szechuan style
directions: In a large soup pot, add water and beef stew meat.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Cover; bring to a boil and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until the meat is tender.
Serve with cooked noodles.
This stew can be frozen.
To make the stew thicker, use 3 1/2 cups water instead of 7 cups.
In a small bowl, mix 3 tablespoons water and 2 1/2 tablespoons cornstarch to make paste. Stir in a little at a time until the sauce becomes clear and thickens.
Garnish with chopped onion or chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix oleo, cocoa, flour, salt, eggs and sugar well.
Add pecans. Bake in 10 x 15-inch pan about 30 minutes or until fork comes out clean.
When cake is done, add a layer of miniature marshmallows and return to oven until melted or light brown.

title: east texas gulf chicken caribbean
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 1-quart shallow casserole. Mix together in a small bowl fruit juice, rum and sugar.
Season chicken with salt and cayenne pepper to taste.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Brown in 10-inch skillet with 4 tablespoons olive oil. Transfer chicken to casserole.
Add green peppers and onion to remaining oil in skillet and saute until clear and lightly browned.
Spread over chicken.
Pour juice mixture over chicken. Bake 30 minutes.

title: ski snacks
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cut English muffins in half.
Spread ingredients on muffins and bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: atlanta pork chops and rice
directions: In large skillet, brown chops in hot oil (375°); remove chops. Add celery, onion and green pepper; cook lightly.
Drain fat. Stir in remaining ingredients; add chops.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Heat milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add mixture to warm milk, stirring constantly.
Add beaten egg yolks, stirring as you add them.
When mixture thickens add peanut butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Meringue on top.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients for about 20 to 30 minutes, until vegetables are done.
While vegetables are cooking, mix flour with melted margarine, over medium-low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook for about 5 minutes, until a light peanut color.
Slowly pour 2 to 3 cups vegetable mixture into flour mixture, stirring vigorously until smooth, then add this back into the rest of soup.
Add Cheez Whiz and Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add warm cream. Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Uncooked balls freeze very well.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and salt and mix well.
Add oatmeal, nuts, dates and chocolate chips.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not bake longer.
Cut in squares.

title: impossible cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Place all ingredients except topping in blender.
Blend on high speed, stopping blender occasionally to stir until smooth (about 3 minutes).
Pour in pie plate.
Bake just until puffed and center is dry, about 30 minutes. (Do not overcook.)
Mix topping and spread carefully over top. Cool.
Refrigerate until chilled, at least 3 hours.
Serve with sweetened fresh fruit, if desired.

title: buckeyes (candy)
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and margarine. Roll into balls and chill.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening in a double boiler over water.
Stick a toothpick in the balls and dip in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper.
Do not completely cover the ball with chocolate.

title: crab burritos(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an ovenproof dish.
In a saucepan, heat oil, add onion and fry until softened.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, cayenne, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes until thickened.
Spread a little sauce over each tortilla.
Sprinkle with crab meat and Mozzarella cheese, then roll up, tucking in the ends.
Put into prepared dish, cover and bake 20 minutes.
Place lettuce on individual serving plates. Peel and slice avocado, brush with lemon juice and arrange on the lettuce.
Place 2 burritos on each plate on top with the tomato sauce and a spoonful of sour cream.
Serve any remaining tomato sauce separately.

title: peruvian aji de gallina(chicken in pepper sauce)
directions: Wash pepper.
Remove centers and soak in water overnight. Grind peppers in food processor or blender.
Remove crusts from bread.
Break up bread and soften in cream.
Brown chicken in oil; remove chicken.
Brown onion and garlic in same pan.
Add chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; add chicken.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese; garnish with eggs and olives before serving.

title: italian baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Season pork chops with garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Add Italian dressing, pepper and onion.
Cover with tinfoil and place in oven.
Cook at 450° to 475° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Check while cooking for water level.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Soak corned beef in water for 2 hours; drain.
Place corned beef and water in Dutch oven; simmer, covered for 3 hours or until tender.
Add potatoes and cabbage, continuing to cook for 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: light spinach dip
directions: Cook, cool and squeeze to drain the spinach.
Combine mayonnaise and milk.
Beat until smooth with wire whisk.
Stir in and blend sour cream.
Add spinach and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors. Serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes 3 2/3 cups.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Combine Crisco, milk and boiling water.
Whip with a fork until like whipped cream.
Add flour and salt and mix.

title: fresh mushroom salad
directions: Blend all ingredients, except mushrooms and lettuce in a large nonaluminum bowl.
Add sliced mushrooms and toss very well. Arrange lettuce on individual serving plates and place mushroom salad in center.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Stir in sauce, beans, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Break the taco shells in half at fold.
Arrange on the bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon mix over the taco shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with shredded lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve.

title: chicken asparagus supreme
directions: Mix bread cubes with grated cheese.
Pour 1/4 cup butter over and mix lightly.
Put 1/2 of mixture in baking dish.
Cook asparagus and set aside.
Place 1/4 cup butter in saucepan; melt. Add flour, salt and pepper; blend well.
Stir in milk and chicken broth and cook, stirring, until thickened and smooth.
Add chicken and lemon juice; blend well.
Place cooked asparagus over bread-cheese-butter mixture in dish.
Top with chicken in sauce. Sprinkle remaining bread cubes-cheese-butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: orange ice cream
directions: To Make Powdered Sugar:
Put granulated sugar in blender; blend on high speed.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Mix water, shortening and salt.
When all ingredients are melted and cool, add 1 beaten egg.
Mix all ingredients well.
Add 3 cups plain unsifted flour.
Knead well with mixture.
Place in the refrigerator overnight, covered.
Let rise and knead again.
Roll out and let rise at least 1 1/2 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° in a preheated oven.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix well and put into a greased casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together except for bread crumbs and put in a casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs with 1 to 2 tablespoons of butter and put on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese(makes 2-quart dish)
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; place in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in milk.
Heat, stirring constantly, until sauce boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in onion and cheese; heat until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth.
Pour over macaroni; dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Cover and place in 375° oven; bake 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken and cheese
directions: Place chicken in large baking dish.
Spoon mixture on each piece of chicken.
Top with 1 slice of Muenster cheese; tuck in edges.
Sprinkle with chives or shallots.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh tomato sauce with brie cheese
directions: In a noncorrosive bowl, place tomatoes, garlic and basil or parsley. Add olive oil and Brie cheese. Stir gently. Leave out of the fridge for at least an hour. Serve over hot pasta. Delicious!

title: sour cream twists
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in butter.
Add yeast (crumbled), sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Mix with hands.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day sprinkle board with 3/4 cup sugar.
Roll dough into 8 x 16-inch rectangle.
Fold two ends toward center and turn, roll again, repeat 4 times to roll all the sugar in.
Finally roll to 1/4-inch and cut in strips.
Twist in forms of a horseshoe twist.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: quick and tasty grilled beef roast
directions: Marinate roast in beefy onion soup mix all day and night (turn often).
Preheat gas grill; sear roast on both sides.
Turn grill to low setting and baste well.
Cook until inside temperature is about 140° to 150°.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Beat eggs; add all ingredients to shredded chicken.
Put in flat Pyrex dish.
Spread crackers or corn flake crumbs over the top.
Bake an hour at 325°.
Use 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Cut cake vertically into halves.
Freeze one half for future use.
Tear other half into small pieces.
Mix pineapple and mandarin oranges. Prepare pudding as directed, except use skim milk.
Layer half each of the cake pieces, fruit mixture and pudding in 2-quart bowl.
Repeat, making approximately 3 layers.
Sprinkle with walnuts and garnish with cherries.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
tags: Betty Crocker white angel food cake mix

title: cooked fudge frosting
directions: Mix ingredients (except vanilla)
in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly, about 1 minute. Cool and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: european beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into strips about 1/4 x 2-inches.
Slice the onion in 1/4-inch slices and then the slices in half.
Melt the butter in a pan and saute the onions and mushrooms.
When the onion is limp, push the mushrooms and onions to one side and add the meat.
Brown it quickly on all sides, takes about 5 minutes.
Then carefully add sour cream, salt and pepper and a dash of mustard, nutmeg and paprika.
When sauce is thoroughly hot, serve over cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: easy bars
directions: Mix together and bake in moderate oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop up cranberries and pour sugar on them.
Let stand.
Make jello and let stay in icebox to chill.
Put all chopped ingredients in and let sit overnight.

title: white clam sauce with linguini
directions: Saute garlic in 1/2 cup olive oil and 1/2 cup butter until golden.
Add clams, clam juice, parsley, salt and lemon juice. Simmer 5 minutes.
Put 1 teaspoon oil or butter in water.
Bring to boil.
Add linguini and cook 6 minutes.
Drain linguini; place on platter.
Pour wine into simmering sauce.
Cook 1 more minute and pour over linguini.
Serves 8.

title: "maw-maw's" chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, plus 1 1/2 cups of crushed crackers. Pour in buttered casserole dish and top with other 1/2 cup of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: caribbean pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil and drain off fat.
Sprinkle onion and garlic over and around chops.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in juice and pour over chops.
Place orange slices and pepper rings on chops.
Simmer covered about 50 minutes or until chops are tender.
Stir sauce and baste occasionally.
Add small amount of water if needed.

title: picadillo
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add salt and garlic powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: country fried steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, using hands.
Mix up another mixture of flour and dry milk (1/2 cup flour and 2 tablespoons milk).
Spread some on rolling board.
Roll meat mixture onto board.
Sprinkle with flour mixture and roll with rolling pin to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes for steaks and fry in hot fat (but not smoking) until just brown.
Do not overcook.
Remove from pan.
Make a thin gravy, return meat to pan and simmer until meat is done.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter, and vanilla in electric blender container. Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased (or Pam sprayed) 9 inch pie pan. Let stand 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes. Watch after 30 minutes, so that pie does not over brown. Serve warm or cold. It makes its own crust.

title: pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze steak.
Cut into strips 2 to 3 inches long. Combine flour with salt and dredge strips; brown in lard drippings in a frying pan.
Pour off fat.
Add 1/2 inch celery pieces and water.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Add can of tomatoes, green pepper (sliced), sliced onion, minced garlic, bay leaf and cayenne pepper.
Cook slowly, covered, for 30 minutes. Serve over noodles.
Can substitute fresh tomatoes.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in 3-cup glass measure. Microwave on High, uncovered, for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes or until mixture starts to boil, stirring once.
Microwave on High, uncovered,
for 5 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips until smooth. Add marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased baking dish (12 x 8-inches), cool until set and cut into squares.

title: swizzle
directions: Drain mandarin syrup into a container and set aside the fruit segments.
Chill the syrup.
When cold, add ginger ale and coloring.
Pour over crushed ice or ice cubes in punch cups, garnish with cherries and mandarin segments.
Serves 10.

title: french coffee lace
directions: Prepare richer sweet dough as you would the sweet dough.
Let rise twice.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Drain and cut up into bite size pieces.
Layer in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup together.
Pour mixture over chicken. Sprinkle poppy seed over soup mixture.
Crumble up Ritz crackers and spread over dish.
Then sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese; add remaining ingredients. Serve with crackers.
Wonderful!

title: spicy pretzels
directions: Mix oil and spices and microwave for 1 minute.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat to boil, then pour over loaves.

title: jeanne's half moon cookies
directions: Mix in order given and beat until smooth.
Drop about 1 1/2 tablespoons in a mound on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 350°.
Frost half the cookie with frosting, the other half with chocolate frosting.

title: spinach salad
directions: Pour sour cream over spinach just before serving.

title: chicken roll-ups and gravy
directions: Put chicken on wax paper.
Flatten to 1/4-inch.
Sprinkle both sides with salt, pepper and garlic.
Place a slice of ham and cheese in center of each chicken roll and secure with toothpicks. Dredge in flour; brown chicken on both sides in oil.
Combine chicken broth, soup and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add beef and cook until done.
Add mushrooms, garlic salt and soup (do not dilute soup).
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add sour cream.

title: south-of-the-border casserole
directions: In small skillet, brown beef in margarine and oil.
Add green pepper and cook until tender.
Put beef and peppers in ungreased 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with onion.
In separate bowl, combine chili with beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, brown sugar, 1 cup corn chips and 1/2 cup cheese.
Stir into beef mixture.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread sour cream over top of casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Make a border of corn chips.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: fried spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine until onion is translucent.
Add ground beef; cook until brown.
Drain off fat. Add spaghetti; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chicken-potato dish
directions: Saute chicken in skillet with a small amount of oil.
Season chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Place sliced potatoes over chicken.
Add cream of mushroom soup over potatoes.
Cover baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve with salad and hot rolls.

title: carrot cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk with butter over low heat. Add cut up fruit, nuts and graham cracker crumbs. Mix well. Pack firm in wax-lined loaf pan. Chill for 2 days.

title: sift, drain, dribble cake
directions: Grease a loaf pan. Drain pineapple well and line pan with it. Sift cake mix over pineapple. Dribble one stick melted margarine over cake mix. (Cover the cake mix with the margarine.) Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. It's good with whipped cream or just plain.

title: barbecue steak supreme
directions: Pound flour into meat.
Cut into serving sizes.
In a skillet, brown meat in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour over cooked rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Cook milk and evaporated milk.
Mix and add remaining ingredients to hot milk and cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Strain and freeze.

title: brown bread(date nut loaf)
directions: Mix fruit and nuts.
Over this pour boiling water and soda. Add sugar and egg, then flour, salt and vanilla.
Bake slowly for 1 hour in a loaf pan, which has been greased.
After one hour, insert knife in loaf.
If it comes out clean, it's done.
Bake at 225°.
Serve with cream cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender; drain.
Add cheese, bread crumbs, margarine, egg, milk, salt and pepper to the cooked squash and onion.
Stir to mix.
Pour into a greased pan. Bake at 350° until firm and slightly brown.

title: banana peach smoothie
directions: Peel and slice banana.
Cut peaches in chunks.
Combine ingredients in electric blender.
Whirl until smooth and fluffy. Yields 10 (1/2 cup each) servings; 44 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: snackers mix
directions: Melt margarine; add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and nuts.
Stir; pour over cereal.
Mix well.
Bake in 250° slow oven for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring 3 to 4 times.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat
topping,	lemonade concentrate and condensed milk in large bowl	of
electric
mixer.
Pour
into
pie shell and chill 1
hour
before serving.
Frozen limeade concentrate may be used in place of lemonade for a lime pie.

title: almond bars
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except almonds and egg white. Pat dough firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush with unbeaten egg white.
Lightly score the top into 24 bars.
Place an almond in center of each bar.
Bake until golden brown in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook shrimp according to package directions.
Plunge into cold water.
If necessary, devein with sharp pointed knife.
Rinse in cold water.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: dukes boston butt
directions: Preheat grill to 350°. Rub meat all over, lightly with salt and pepper. Sprinkle liberally with butt rub.
Place on hot grill. In one hour, turn to 300° and cook until bone shows. In about 3 1/2 hours, 1/2 inch of bone will show.
Remove from grill.	Cool 30 minutes. Shred or slice.
Serves 10.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Mix together first six ingredients.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Pour sauce over and bake for approximately 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop in food processor.
Pour boiling water over relish and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: strawberry poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box, baking in well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Poke with a fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

title: hawaiian hamburgers
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and celery, cook 5 minutes.
Drain grease.
Place in 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle rice and soy sauce over meat mixture.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with noodles.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Put in half of bread cubes. Put cream cheese cubes over bread cubes.
Put rest of bread cubes over cheese.
Beat together Egg Beaters, maple syrup, cinnamon and milk.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Cover with foil.
Put in fridge overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Uncover bread and bake for 35 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on a cookie sheet.
While cake is cooling, drain the crushed pineapple well.
Mix softened cream cheese with pineapple juice and milk, add pudding and mix until thickened.
Pour over cake and then put crushed pineapple on top of pudding mixture.
Put Cool Whip over top of this and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate.

title: date oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, salt and soda and spices; sift twice.
Cream the butter, gradually add the sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add the beaten eggs to the creamed mixture and stir in the oats and milk.
Sift the flour over the dates, coconut and nuts and mix well.
Stir into the oatmeal mixture, mix in thoroughly.
Drop by small tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet, 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until delicately browned. Yields about 3 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter. Slowly add milk.
Fold in topping.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze until firm.

title: twistin' pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, blend dressing, mustard and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover; chill thoroughly. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding by directions on box; add sour cream, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer with bananas (and pineapple) and vanilla wafers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together, add nuts last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (see Sally's Pie Crust).
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.

title: charlotte russe
directions: Line 1
quart mold with ladyfingers split in half.
Add gelatin to
water.
Beat egg yolks with sugar.
Slowly stir in milk, then
add softened gelatin.
Stir over medium heat for 1 minute.
Chill
until
slightly
thickened.
Blend
in
lemon juice, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Chill in mold until firm.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet over medium heat; add mushrooms and onion.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add wine and cook 1 minute.
Add beef broth and pepper; simmer 5 minutes, or until liquid is reduced to half.	Mix 2 tablespoons flour with tablespoon melted butter.
Add to sauce, stirring until sauce thickens. Season to taste.
Yield 3 cups.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Use orange jello dry. Classified as salad, but it makes a light and different dessert.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine yeast, beer and sugar in mixing bowl.
Allow to stand until yeast is dissolved and begins to foam (about 5 minutes).
Stir in salt and flour.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead 5 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.
Separate dough into 12 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into 20 inch long rope and form pretzel shape.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with kosher salt.
Bake 15 minutes until golden brown.
Remove and cool.

title: meringue for pie
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat the egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar at medium speed of an electric mixer about 1 minute or until soft peaks form.
Gradually add the sugar, about 1 tablespoon at a time, beating at high speed of electric mixer about 4 minutes or until mixture forms stiff, glossy peaks and sugar is dissolved.
Immediately spread meringue over pie, carefully sealing to edge of pastry to prevent shrinkage.
Bake at directed in individual pie recipe.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients by hand in a large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: bachelor's chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken and stock in a pot and bring to a boil. Pinch each biscuit into 4 or 5 pieces and drop into the stock. Cook about 5 or 6 minutes. This receipt is easy to double.

title: easy apple strudel
directions: Cut butter into flour and salt as for pie crust.
Mix together egg yolks, vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture, mixing with fork.
Add a little more flour as needed to make a heavy dough that can be handled.
Chill dough several hours or overnight. Roll out thin and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Spread with apples.
Add flour, cinnamon and butter mixture.
Roll up as jelly roll.
Seal edges well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2.

title: barbecued potatoes
directions: Spread out tinfoil in double layers.
Spray lightly with Pam. Slice potatoes thin.
Dice 1 onion.
Fold remaining ingredients together and put on grill on low to medium heat.
Use fork to check when done.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water and let cool.
Mix oil, salt, sugar and flour.
Mix well with yeast mixture.
Cover with a towel and put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out as much as you need to make a pan of rolls.
Let rise one hour in a warm place, after cutting or shaping into rolls.
Put in cold oven.
Turn on to 350° and bake until brown.

title: rice supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Season well.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 375°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: date bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and add butter when cool.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for one hour.

title: beef and wine casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole and cover.
Bake for 3 hours at 325°.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and green peppers slowly in oil until onions are yellow.
Add hamburger and saute until mixture falls apart.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Arrange in large casserole and cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peach delight(also good with strawberries)
directions: Mix; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: six layer casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Put a layer of sliced potatoes first in casserole, then layer remaining ingredients.
Use the juice of tomatoes and see that it goes to bottom of casserole.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas-style short ribs
directions: Thoroughly combine catsup, soy sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, chili powder and pepper sauce; set aside.
Coat ribs with flour; brown on all sides in hot oil.
Drain off excess fat.
Pour catsup mixture evenly over ribs; sprinkle onion pieces over sauce. Cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned cream filling
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and place in double boiler.
Stir in 1/3 cup milk and egg yolks. Mix and stir; add remaining milk.
Cook until thick, then add butter and vanilla.

title: elegant apple cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter flavoring.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Frost with a cream cheese icing.

title: meat dip
directions: Combine beef and sausage.
Brown and drain.
Melt cheese in microwave.
Add soup and relish to meat.
Then add cheese and mix. Serve warm.

title: chocolate fillers
directions: Cream margarine or butter with brown sugar and salt.
Blend in flour and oats until particles are fine.
Press 2/3 of mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir in chips.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs; press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until light brown.

title: summer blt spread
directions: Reserve 1 teaspoon bacon for garnish.
Combine remaining bacon, sour cream, mayonnaise and plum tomatoes in medium bowl, stirring until blended.

title: cherry or apricot bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add oats and brown sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Press 2/3 mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread generously with preserves.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture and press in place. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while still warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, pepper, soup, carrots and seasoning with sour cream.
Leaving enough to sprinkle over top, combine dressing with melted margarine.
Combine squash mixture with dressing mixture in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining dressing on top; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy spinach souffle
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients except the spinach and rice; blend well.
Fold into the blended ingredients the cooked and drained spinach and the rice.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown around the edges.

title: house rolls
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large bowl. Add the margarine with mixer at low speed.
Pour 2 cups hot water into this.
Add egg; increase speed to medium.
Beat 2 minutes. Beat in 3/4 cup flour; beat 2 minutes more.
Spoon-stir in 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour to make soft dough.
Knead 4 to 5 minutes.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rest for 15 minutes, covered.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce, cabbage leaves and water.
Roll into meat balls.
Place into cabbage leaves.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Cook in large pot.
Pour water over meat balls.
Cover; let cook until cabbage is almost done.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer on low 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter. Sprinkle pecans on bottom of crust.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: heavenly hash browns
directions: Mix together.
Reserve some butter to drizzle on top.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put crushed corn flakes on top (optional) 10 minutes before finished.

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain. Combine all ingredients except lettuce and cheese.
Cover and chill.
Toss with lettuce and cheese just before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together green beans and mushroom soup.
Spread onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave 2 minute fudge
directions: In large casserole dish, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla.
Put butter over top.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in nuts.
Pour onto waxed paper-lined 10 x 7-inch loaf pan.
Chill one hour.
Cut into squares.
(If candy is hard or brittle, let warm to room temperature before cutting.)

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all together; beat well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Mix pineapple juice (or orange juice) with 1/2 box of 10x confectioners sugar.
Pour over hot cake in pan.

title: eggplant "a la parilla"
directions: Roast eggplant and peppers on charcoal grill as follows: The grill should be medium hot.
Place the vegetables on grill and rotate every 2 or 3 minutes to heat all around.
Eggplant will begin to steam and the steam will escape from a rupture in skin. Stop rotating.
When the vegetables are tender, remove them from grill and cool.
Remove skin and seeds from pepper and eggplant. Add pimentos to peppers.
Add salt, pepper, oil and vinegar to taste.

title: tender barbecue chicken(in slow cooker)
directions: May substitute lemon juice for 1 medium lemon; chile sauce for barbecue sauce.

title: okra fritter
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; stir in okra.
Pour oil to depth of 2 inches into a Dutch oven; heat to 350°.
Drop mixture by tablespoonful into oil and cook until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve immediately.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into 1 inch balls.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Mix altogether and serve.

title: easy fresh pickle slices
directions: Combine cucumber, green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and celery seed.
Combine sugar with vinegar until dissolved and pour over cucumbers.
Stir gently to blend.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with ice and let stand 3 hours, then drain.
In a large boiler, put sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Let this come to a boil.
Add the cucumbers and onions.
Let this boil.
Add cinnamon and cloves to taste.
Put in jars and seal.

title: escalloped eggplant
directions: Peeled and diced eggplant is used.
Cook this in salted, boiling water until tender.
Drain well.
Place a layer in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Add a layer of sliced tomatoes.
Repeat until dish is full.
Cover top with bread crumbs and sharp cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° until crumbs are brown and cheese is melted.

title: low-fat dip
directions: Good with vegetables and potato chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix up the night before needed and put in refrigerator.
Take out and put in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake for 15 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: With large mixer, blend sweet potatoes, milk, sugar, margarine, eggs and salt.
Pour into well-buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and nuts that have been mixed together.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Drain blueberries and pineapple; reserve liquids. Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water. Add enough water to reserved liquid to make 1 3/4 cups.	Add to Jell-O. Pour into 13 x 9 pan and allow to gel slightly; add fruit.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove dough from cans but do not unroll. Cut each roll into 12 slices.
Bake for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove from oven and spoon 1 teaspoon of sauce on roll.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven and bake 3 to 5 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water until it forms a hard ball in cool water (250° to 260°).
Add unblanched peanuts and continue to cook until mixture turns golden brown.
Remove from heat and stir in butter or margarine and salt.
Stir in soda.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: Put ribs and potatoes in pot on stove top burner.
Stir remaining ingredients together and pour mixture over ribs and potatoes.
Cover and cook about 2 hours on medium-high heat, stirring occasionally.

title: melt in your mouth fried pie pastry
directions: Combine flour, soda and baking powder; cut in Crisco until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add egg and buttermilk to flour mixture.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth.
Using a 5-inch saucer, maker circles and place fruit mixture on half of each pastry circle.

title: carrot pecan cake(bob's favorite)
directions: Combine oil and sugar. Mix well.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Sift half into oil and sugar mixture.
Blend.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle onions on top about 5 minutes before casserole is done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix half the sugar with cornstarch, flour and salt.
Add lemon rind.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook in heavy pan or double boiler, continuing to stir until thick and clear.
Mix remaining sugar with egg yolks and lemon juice; add to first mixture.
Cook 2 minutes longer until thick and smooth.
Add butter.
Cool.

title: no-bake cheesecake(lower fat than regular)
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in yogurt and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours. Garnish with fresh fruit, if desired.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Crumble sausage in a skillet and cook until done; drain on paper towel.
Return sausage to skillet, stir in rice and cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes, until rice is golden, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chinese duck
directions: Combine spices in a large pot.
Add duck and enough water to cover.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Remove duck from pot, reserving 2 cups broth.
Heat 1/2-inch oil in a
large frying pan and fry duck on each side about 5 minutes until well browned.
Cool duck.
Remove meat from the bones in as large pieces as possible.
Dip the duck in egg and then in crumbs before frying in the same oil.
Cut duck into 2-inch pieces and serve over Chinese vegetables.
Top with lettuce and onions.
If desired, make gravy with the reserved duck broth and 4 tablespoons flour and serve on the side with rice. Serves 3 to 4.

title: hot sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend just long enough to mix together (a few seconds).
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook bacon and onion together until bacon and onion are brown. Add potatoes and enough water (about 1 1/2 inches) over mixture. Cook until potatoes fall apart.
Add half and half.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: rock pie
directions: *Use granola cereal, chocolate chips and peanut butter chips as your rocks.

title: apricot coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs well one at a time.
Fold in sour cream and almond extract.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; fold into creamed mixture.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients. Using hands, roll dough into cookies. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle nuts on cookies, if using. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 300°. Makes 24 cookies.

title: minted jello salad
directions: Drain and reserve mandarin orange juice.
Heat orange juice with mint leaves and steep 10 minutes.
Strain leaves and bring juice to boiling and pour over Jell-O.
Add other cup of juice and chill until slightly thickened.
Add oranges and cantaloupe balls. Pour in Jell-O mold.

title: lattice-top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Place in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered with foil, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Roll into a ball.
Put into freezer until firm. Roll in chopped nuts.

title: french onion soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, saute onions in margarine over low heat until onions are tender.
Stir in beef broth, bouillon cube, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine cheeses.
Ladle soup into ovenproof bowl. Top each with French bread and top with 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.
Place under oven broiler for 1 to 3 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Serve hot.
Place bowls on cookie sheet for easy broiling.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased tube pan.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients (flour, soda and salt). Cream together shortening and sugar (white and brown).
Add one at a time, beating well after each addition, the 2 eggs.
Stir in nuts, chips, oatmeal, vanilla, hot water and sifted dry ingredients. Mix well by hand and drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: vegetable chip dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: fresh orange loaf cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into large bowl.
Add shortening and orange juice.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes with electric mixer on slow to medium speed.
Add eggs and beat 2 more minutes. Pour into greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: cookie ice cream cake
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze 20 minutes or until firm.
Spread slightly softened ice cream over crust.
Freeze 20 minutes or until firm.
Spread fudge topping over ice cream.
Freeze 20 minutes.

title: oven fried haddock
directions: Soak haddock in milk and drain.
Place in greased baking dish (Pyrex) or pan.
Add crumbs; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in a 525° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cook on the top shelf.

title: traditional spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in large saucepan.
Add garlic and stir.
Add sausage and brown.
Add onions and tomatoes and stir, cooking, for 4 minutes.
Mix in wine, tomato paste and sugar.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in fresh oregano and remove from heat.
Serve over cooked pasta.
Serves 6.

title: 3-layer chocolate delight pie
directions: Combine these ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Press into pie pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients well and add vinegar and water.
Cook on stove until thick.
Add butter when removed from stove.
Add some pepper to taste.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Good on garden lettuce.

title: crusty coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut and let set until you cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add milk, coconut and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: tuna or chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except lemon Jell-O.
Mix lemon Jell-O with boiling water and then mix with other ingredients.

title: mexican dip with tortilla chips
directions: Layer in order given and chill until serving time.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: meatballs and rice
directions: Pour tomato juice into a large pan.
Add chopped onion, green pepper, sliced carrots and celery.
Heat on medium-high while adding meatballs.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute first three ingredients in a three-quart saucepan over medium heat until lightly brown, stirring occasionally.
Add crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, basil or oregano, salt and water. Simmer uncovered until thickened, about 30 minutes on low heat. Pour over hot cooked spaghetti.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture of milk, sugar and flour into pan.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus and cut into 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes, drain and set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in flour and cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk, cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Add salt and pepper.
Arrange half of asparagus in 8-inch square greased baking dish.
Top with egg slices and half of white sauce. Repeat with rest of asparagus then white sauce. Combine cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meatball vegetable soup
directions: Combine meat, cracker crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper and form into 20 meatballs.
Brown in oil over medium heat.
In medium saucepan, combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, onion soup mix and sugar.
Add meatballs and vegetables.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add buttermilk, sugar and cooking oil.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to liquid, 1 cup at a time; mix well.
Cover with foil; set in refrigerator overnight.
Dip out as much as needed.
Make into small biscuits and bake.
You do not have to wait for them to rise.

title: brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients first, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in a well oiled 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish at 350°.

title: lo-cal spice tea
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.
Add 2 or 3 teaspoons per 1 cup of boiling water.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in airtight container. Fill cup approximately 1/4 full of mix. Add boiling water and stir. Great for camping or for quick cup of cocoa.

title: butterscotch frozen pies
directions: Mix cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Pour into pie shells. Brown coconut in margarine (in black skillet). Spread over top of pies, then drizzle butterscotch topping over all. Chill well before freezing. Pies freeze well and are good when served almost frozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Bake at 350 for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ambrosia mold(makes 10 servings)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin; dissolve completely.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes more or until mixture will slightly mound.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold.

title: fast pizza crust
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, undissolved yeast and salt. Stir to blend.
Add hot tap water, oil and honey.
Stir to blend. Cover with plastic wrap and let rise 10 minutes.
Place in greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Press to cover bottom of pan and up sides.
Spread with your choice of sauce, seasonings and toppings. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken ala john sawaya
directions: Vine leaves should be picked when they have a light green color and should be medium size, not too large and not too small. After picking, stems have to be removed with a sharp knife cutting at the place where the stem meets the leaf.
If using fresh, leaves should be blanched in boiling water for a few seconds and drained on paper towels.
Leaves can be frozen by taking fresh leaves, wiping with a damp cloth and put into freezer bags in rolls of 50 or so.

Frozen leaves do not have to be blanched but should be thoroughly defrosted before use or they will tear. Leaves can also be "canned" by using a brine which is made with cold water and enough salt to float a raw egg.
Roll leaves in bundles, tie with string, and place four or five bundles in a jar, filling with brine.
Be sure seal does not leak and no air bubbles appear.
Leaves can also be purchased in jars which have been in brine; these leaves must be washed and dried on paper towels before use.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Select and cut chicken as for frying.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper chicken. Dip each piece of chicken in sauce and place in aluminum foil.
Pour remaining sauce over it and fold up tightly.
Place in roaster. Cover and place in a 500° oven.
Cook for 15 minutes. Turn oven down to 350° and cook an additional 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ruby's chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa and milk; cook on medium heat after boiling. Boil 15 minutes or until tested in water and makes a soft ball. Take off heat; add oleo and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and begins to get thick.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet or pan.

title: pretzel strawberry dessert salad
directions: Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes and cool.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain all vegetables; toss together.
Mix the vinegar, water, salt, sugar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand for a while and refrigerate.

title: herb cracker snacks
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place oyster crackers in large bowl.
In small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients.
Drizzle mixture over crackers, toss gently to coat.
Spread mixture evenly in ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 14 to 16 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring occasionally.
Cool completely.

title: chicken a la king casserole
directions: Mix chicken a la king and soup powder in a saucepan.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Add to chicken a la king mixture and toss to coat pasta.
This is good served with any pasta or rice.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash bean mix.
Place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans and soak overnight.
Drain beans and add 2 quarts water with ham, onion, garlic and salt.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer another 30 minutes or more, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: gingerbread treats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix water and molasses; mix flour, soda, baking powder, ginger and salt.
Add to water, molasses mixture.
Add shortening and raisins, then mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tuna patties
directions: Combine tuna fish, salt, pepper, garlic salt, chopped onion, chopped parsley, chopped celery and corn flake crumbs; add beaten eggs and milk and mix thoroughly.
Shape into patties.
Fry in Crisco oil until golden brown, about 6 to 7 minutes on medium heat.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: sugar rum pecans
directions: Cook together the sugar and canned milk until a drop hardens when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Pour in the rum extract; mix well.
Pour in pecan halves; mix well to coat.
Pour coated pecans into a large, covered container containing the powdered sugar.
Shake well until all pecans are coated with sugar.
Store in an airtight container.

title: cinnamon icebox cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Add nuts. Form into rolls and freeze.
Slice and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: old-time egg noodles
directions: Combine eggs and salt; beat until foamy.
Add butter and flour.
Mix into stiff dough.
Divide into halves; round each half into ball.
Roll on lightly floured board or cloth.
Let dry slightly; cut into strips.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix everything together (in order), one at a time.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or longer until golden brown.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch squares. Double the recipe for 50 people.

title: wontons(wahn-tahns)
directions: Cook onion and green pepper.
Add hamburger; drain.
Wash bean sprouts and add to hamburger.
Add beef cubes, celery salt and soy sauce.
Wrap the mix in egg roll wraps (large) and deep fry.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add beaten eggs to sausage and scramble.
Top with grated cheese and spoon jar of picante sauce on top.
Heat tortillas in bag in microwave until warm.

title: chocolate fondue with fruit
directions: Melt and stir.
Fantastic with apples, strawberries, bananas, melon, etc.

title: thimble cookies(lorie's favorite)
directions: Mix together and chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.	Roll teaspoon of dough into ball and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flour thimble and punch hole in middle of cookie, being careful not to break ball. Fill with jelly.

title: french dressing
directions: Put into blender; mix well.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt butterscotch chips with peanut butter in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies, stirring until well coated with butterscotch mixture.
Press half of mixture into buttered pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Chill in fridge while preparing fudge mixture.
Set remaining cereal mixture aside.
Combine chocolate chips, sugar, water and butter; stir over hot water until chocolate melts and mixture is well blended.
Spread over chilled butterscotch mixture. Spread reserved mixture on top; press in gently.
Chill!
Remove from refrigerator for about 10 minutes before cutting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add strawberries.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with yogurt.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pile high in crust and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, garnish with fresh fruit.
Serves 8.

title: deep fried tofu
directions: Drain the tofu and carefully cut into 2-inch cubes.
Dust tofu cubes lightly with flour.
Heat the cooking oil on high until very hot.
Gently add the tofu cubes.
Lightly brown on all sides. Quickly remove from oil and place on paper towels to absorb any excess oil.
Place the cubes in individual serving dishes and pour sauce over the top of the tofu and garnish.

title: rolled beef
directions: Place round steak on wax paper.
On it, layer the onions, pork, bread crumbs, Romano cheese, parsley, spinach, cold cuts, cheese, peas and sliced eggs.
Leave space around edges to allow for rolling.
Roll steak and tie with string.
Brown in olive oil. Add chicken broth, tomato paste and wine.
Simmer on top of stove for 35 minutes.

title: pecan cream pie
directions: Beat eggs, milk and syrup; cook until thick.
Boil 3 minutes; cool.
Pour into crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: I add more coffee creamer, powdered sugar and Nestle to make richer.
Store in Tupperware.
Use 1/4 cup to hot water.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix in large bowl:
green beans, wax beans, onion, green pepper, pimentos, water chestnuts and celery.
In saucepan, combine salad oil, honey, cider vinegar and water.
Bring to boil. Pour over bean mixture.
Let stand 6 hours in refrigerator. Serves 6.

title: grandma marley's chow chow
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers together and let stand. Drain.
Add the hot peppers, which have been chopped, the vinegar and spices (spices tied in cheesecloth bag).
Allow to boil slowly until tender (about 15 minutes).
Pack tightly into hot Mason or Kerr canning jars and seal at once.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add butter and mix again.
Arrange pecans in bottom of unbaked crust. Pour mixture over them.
Bake in 375° oven about 1 hour.
Pecans should rise to the top.

title: alaskan bakeless cake
directions: Line bottom of buttered 9 x 9-inch pan with layer of crumbs, reserving 2 or 3 tablespoons crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Spoon on top of crumbs.
Fold drained pineapple into whipped cream and spread over first mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.

title: chili and meatballs(with cornmeal dumplings)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine meat, 1/4 cup onions, bread crumbs, egg, 3 teaspoons bouillon and 1 teaspoon of chili powder.
Mix well.
Shape into meatballs (1 1/2-inch in size).
Roll in flour and brown in skillet.
Drain and set aside.
In slow cooker, combine remaining ingredients, except for beans and dumplings. Stir in meatballs.
Cover and cook on low setting in microwave or over stove burner.
Stir in beans.
Cook on high 15 minutes before adding dumplings.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle.
Mix evaporated milk and cream of coconut together; pour over cake.
When cake is completely cool, spread over with Cool Whip.
Top with shredded coconut.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cream cheese pie(serves 6)
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and vanilla well with mixer. Pour in graham cracker pie crust. Garnish with cherry pie filling on top.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Put Bisquick, milk and eggs in blender and blend.
Spray a pie pan with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place broccoli and onions in pan.
Put cheese on top of broccoli and add salt.
Pour blended ingredients on top.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: a mama's stuffed pork loin
directions: Cut 2 1/2 inch wide pocket in pork loin.
Mix cream cheese and apricots, stuff pocket with mixture.
Tie loin back together with kitchen string.
Combine herbs, salt, pepper and oil.
Rub on outside of pork loin.
Place loin, fat side up, in roasting pan. Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325 degrees until meat thermometer registers 165 degrees.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: midwest vegetable crunch
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except bacon bits. Cover and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, for at least 4 hours.
Just before serving, toss with bacon bits.

title: neapolitan spumone
directions: Combine milk, 1 cup sugar, egg yolks and flavoring extracts. Cook, stirring, until custard begins to boil.
Chill in freezer until softly frozen.
Fold in half whipped cream.
Divide into 2 equal parts.
To 1 part, add green food coloring.
To the other, add red food coloring, cherries, almonds and orange peel.
Freeze partially, about 1 hour, stirring now and then, until spreading consistency.
Mix remaining whipped cream with 1/4 cup sugar, cocoa and rum.
Chill.

title: special cabbage
directions: Place
cabbage in shallow 4 quart casserole.
Pour milk over; sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Cover; bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned and cabbage is tender.	Makes 6 generous servings.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Cook ingredients, stirring constantly.
This will be very thick.
Cool completely.
Add 1 cup sour cream.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: mushroom in cream
directions: In medium bowl combine flour and salt.
Use pastry blender or 2 knives.
Cut in cream cheese and butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Knead dough.
Divide in half and wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill one hour.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
In another bowl, beat sugar, shredded zucchini and egg. Add oil and lemon peel.
Mix well.
Stir flour mixture into zucchini mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Put batter in a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: grape jelly from frozen juice
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, blend together grape juice concentrate and pectin.
Stir in water.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 8 to 9 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes, until bubbles form around edge of dish.
Add sugar, mixing well.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes, until mixture boils.
Then time for 1 full minute of boiling.
Stir and skim off foam with metal spoon.
Ladle into prepared jelly glasses and seal.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Layer potatoes slices, onion slices, small pieces of cheese, pepper and salt.
Dot with margarine and bake in covered 8 x 8 inch casserole dish at 325° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Arrange alternate layers of cooked noodles, tuna and soup in greased casserole. Begin and end with noodles. Cover with 1/2 cup soft bread crumbs or potato chips. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: passover chocolate nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray entire inner surface of 10-inch pie plate.
Set aside.
Combine all ingredients except cherries, strawberries and powdered sugar in a food processor.
Blend on high for 1 minute.

Pour a thin layer of the batter into the pan and place it in the center of the preheated oven for 8 minutes. While the pie plate is in the oven, combine the drained cherries and strawberries in a bowl with the powdered sugar.
Mix well. Remove pie plate from oven and place on a cookie sheet.
Spoon the cherry-berry mixture, spreading evenly.
Pour remaining batter evenly over the top.
Carefully place baking sheet in oven and bake about 1 hour or until clafouti is puffed up and browned. Remove from oven and allow to cool at least 30 minutes before slicing.
As it cools, the clafouti will lose some of its puffiness and flatten out.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cornmeal, eggs, sugar and milk together.
Measure 1 1/2 tablespoons of margarine in the skillet. Put 1 teaspoon of flour in the skillet to keep from sticking. Pour batter into the skillet and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Brown the top to darken.

title: lemon extract cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add the extract and blend.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Add to the creamed mixture; add fruits and nuts.
Bake in loaf pans at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and grated cheese.
Chop onion and cabbage and dice tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and stir.
Add taco sauce, then crush Fritos.
Mix all together and serve hot or warm as when it cools, Fritos get mushy.

title: imperial fried rice
directions: Cook rice as package directs.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings. Stir in rice and onions.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soy sauce.
Season to taste with pepper.
Add vegetables; gently toss.
Cover; heat through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
