directions: Dissolve sugar in vinegar. Add mustard, salt and poppy seed. Slowly add oil and beat until thick.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Layer vegetables in pan as follows:
carrots, celery, onion, potatoes and rice.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over top.
Add bay leaves.
Season ground beef with a touch of garlic salt and pepper. Make 12 hamburger patties.
Place on top of casserole.
Top all with canned tomatoes.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put chopped pecans and shredded coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to package directions.
Put on top of nuts and coconut.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and butter. Spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: marie's pasta salad
directions: Boil rotini according to the package.
Cut broccoli into florets; place in boiling water for 1 minute and drain.
Slice peppers and onion thin, julienne style.
Mix all ingredients with the dressing.
Reserve some of the pepperoni to arrange on top. Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Remove 15 minutes before serving.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat wok or large frying pan.
Add oil.
Stir-fry green onions.
Add eggs.
When cooking eggs and onions, cook as scrambling eggs; keep eggs moist.
Push to side of pan.
Add peas and carrots.
Add meat; mix together.
Keep stirring.
Add rice. Make sure rice and egg mixture are all broken up.
Can be made in advance, but leave vegetables out because it has a tendency to change color.
Keep in warm oven at 150°.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Steam broccoli 5 minutes; set aside.
Combine
soup, sour cream, grated carrot, minced onion and flour.
Fold in broccoli. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine. Sprinkle around edges of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Pour into tube pan and bake for 45 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar glaze or excellent without icing.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Add your egg and butter.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups half full.
Bake for 25 minutes in 375° oven.

title: blackberry applesauce cobbler
directions: Sift mix to remove nuggets.
Blend nuggets, applesauce and flour.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Combine muffin mix and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over nugget mixture.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Beat egg whites, margarine, sifted powdered sugar and vanilla. Beat until very fluffy.
Put on top of crust mixture and refrigerate 30 minutes or longer.

title: meal-in-a-dish
directions: In a baking dish, place 3 or 4 layers of Irish potatoes (sliced) and about 2 layers of sliced onions.
Salt to taste.
Add cream-style corn and blobs of catsup.
Top with sausage patties.

title: merry berry cheese bars(24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. With mixer, beat flour, oats and 3/4 cup sugar and butter until crumbly.

Set aside 1 1/2 cups mixture. Press remaining mixture on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned. With mixer, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth; stir in lemon juice. Spread over baked crust.

title: pretty pink salad
directions: Place pineapple and sugar in sauce pan; bring to a boil.
Add jello; cool.
Whip the cream and fold into cooled jello mixture. Fold in cottage cheese and bananas.
Pour in salad mold and chill.

title: frozen daiquiri
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large container.
Place in the freezer for 24 hours before serving.
Stir into a slushy consistency.
Makes 30 one-half cup servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
While this cooks, mix rest of ingredients and cook as directed on pudding box.
Cool about 15 minutes.
Mix pudding and rice.
Chill and serve.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to instructions on package.
Cool. Punch holes with fingers.
Fill holes with Kahlua.
Allow to absorb.
Cut pan of brownies in half.
Begin with brownie and layer mousse, candy and Cool Whip.
Repeat layer.
Garnish with chopped Heath bars or shaved chocolate.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.

title: quick pizza from leftovers
directions: Grease pan with olive oil.
Spread out dough.
It will shrink back slightly.
Lightly brush with olive oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in preheated 475° oven for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Add sauce and chopped vegetables and toppings.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes small 2 person pizza.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, melted butter, pecans and 2 eggs.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes. Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester is dry.
Let set 10 minutes, then carefully remove from pan.

title: homemade mustard
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon together and let sit 5 hours.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar in a shakable container. Shake well until blended.
Add mayo mixture to broccoli mixture and stir.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together sour cream and mayonnaise, then add herbs and mix thoroughly.
Chill and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all above.
Pour in shallow casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Add topping and return to oven for an additional 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, broccoli and onion.
Mix vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over the vegetables.
Toss well and refrigerate for at least
1 hour before serving.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done.
Cut into chunks.
Mix all ingredients but meat, cheese and chips in a bowl.
Layer in a casserole the mixture, chicken, cheese and chips.
Continue layers until filled.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with fresh, steamed asparagus and a garden salad.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend orange juice and pudding mix in blender.
Add Dream Whip and blend.

title: no cook ice cream
directions: Beat all together until well blended.
Pour into ice cream container and finish filling with regular milk to line.
Alternate ice and ice cream salt around container and let it make until hard to turn if manual or it stops if electric.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and serve as a dip for fresh fruit or angel food cake cubes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Note:
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: mock shepherd's pie
directions: Brown onion in skillet in small amount of hot fat.
Add beef, salt and pepper.
Cook until browned.
Drain beans.
Add to beef mixture with soup.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Mash potatoes; add milk and egg.
Add additional salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon in mounds over beef mixture.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: two-step chicken divan
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole, arrange broccoli. Top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 6 minutes or until hot.
Rotate halfway through cooking.

title: tangy tortellini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Cheddar cheese and lettuce) and
a pinch of Tabasco sauce to taste.
Top with Cheddar cheese and lettuce.
Chill and marinate whole salad before serving.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix until light.
Add beaten eggs; mix.
Put coffee, molasses and grape juice in separate bowl and mix thoroughly; add to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Sift flour with cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon and baking soda.
In a separate, very large bowl add candied mixed fruit, raisins, currants, almonds, walnuts, chopped dates and dredge with flour; mix thoroughly.
Add the egg mixture and mix well.
Add sifted flour mixture and thoroughly mix.
Grease and flour 5 (9 x 5-inch) foil loaf pans.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Cream margarine, cheese, flour, salt and red pepper until thoroughly blended; stir in Rice Krispies.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Use about 1/2 teaspoon of batter per cookie.
Makes about 135.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and salt.
Stir well.
Add 2 cups milk, Velveeta cheese, Cheddar cheese and bouillon cube.
Cook potatoes, onion, celery and carrots.
Drain and add to cheese sauce.
Add 3 more cups of milk.

title: maple syrup for pancakes and waffles
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil; boil about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add flavoring.

title: pie crust made easy
directions: Mix well.
Press out with fingers into bottom of a large pie plate; flute edge.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Do not prick pie shell!

title: perfect brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat after each. Add vanilla, then melted chocolate; mix. Add flour. Add nuts now or save and put on top before baking. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes in an 8 x 8 greased pan.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put 24 balls on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and chill for 12 hours.
May be made 2 to 3 days ahead and refrigerated.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: rice and sausage dressing
directions: Cook celery, onion and sausage over medium-low heat until done or about 20 minutes.
Boil water, soup and rice together for 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 4-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato bread sticks
directions: In small saucepan, heat reserved potato water to 120° to 130°.

title: fresh apple cake with hard sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool in brown paper bag (leave cake in pan).

title: wine punch
directions: In a 1 gallon container, combine first 4 ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Stir in cherries.
Cover and chill overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve chilled.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Put all in pan and bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil for 5 minutes (no more, no less).
Makes about 3 pints.
Can be frozen.

title: fruity cranberry relish
directions: In a food processor, combine cranberries and orange sections. Cover and process until chopped. Transfer to a bowl; add apples, pineapple, sugar, grapes, orange peel and salt. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Stir in the walnuts just before serving. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake at 350° until set (about 45 minutes).

title: browned mush
directions: Pour the mush, while hot, in a small deep pan, first rinsed with cold water.
When cold, turn out, slice crosswise and then in halves.
Dip each piece in fine dry crumbs, then in the egg slightly beaten with one-fourth cup cold water, then in crumbs again.
In the meantime, heat enough Mazola in a deep fat frying kettle to half fill it.
Put slices in a frying pan and fry until golden brown in the Mazola which should be hot enough to brown a bit, 375° by the frying thermometer.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 c. boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Fold in cool whip.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.
Serve in crystal bowl.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients, add enough water to desired consistency. (Like pancakes for heavy breading - thin for light and crispy.) Deep fry on medium-high for 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown. Drain.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add soup and 1 can of water.
Add cheese until melted.
Combine rest.
Pour into casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs or crushed Ritz crackers (also buttered).
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: potato bacon casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a 9-inch baking dish. Layer 1/2 the potatoes, 1/2 the onion, 1/2 the bacon and 1/2 the cheese; repeat layers. Combine the evaporated milk, egg and salt in a bowl. Pour evenly over potato mixture and bake, covered, for 50 minutes. Bake, uncovered, another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add flour, pepper and salt.
Work in Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: brown crisps
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg, dry ingredients and nuts.
Form into rolls; chill, slice and bake at 325°.
The dough can be dropped onto a greased cookie sheet and baked as dropped cookies.

title: inside-out ravioli
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients.
Drain frozen spinach and save liquid.
Combine spinach, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Add 1/2 cup liquid from spinach.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Add spinach mixture, pasta, cheese, bread crumbs, eggs and salad oil.
Spread pasta mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with meat sauce.
(Sometimes there is too much for 1 pan.
I put extra in an 8 x 8-inch pan and freeze.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Heat sugar, vinegar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables and mix well. Chill.

title: spanish black beans
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in large bowl.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak overnight.
Saute green peppers, onions and garlic in olive oil until tender.
Drain beans; stir in vegetables and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; reduce heat to low and cook, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove ham hock and bay leaves from beans; scrape meat from bone.
Add meat and vinegar to beans; stir well.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings. Serve with shredded Mozzarella cheese and/or sour cream, if desired.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, heat spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella, Parmesan and parsley. Pour 3/4 cup sauce in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange 3 pieces uncooked lasagne lengthwise over sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining pasta and sauce; sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil; bake for 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mom's seafoam salad
directions: Heat pear juice; pour over jello.
Pour over the cream cheese which has been mashed with the cream.
When cool and thick, add the pears.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Chill.
(I always double the recipe.)

title: corn bread cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer each vegetable, adding salad dressing evenly on top. Spread evenly with the back of a spoon.
Sprinkle with bacon bits. Serve chilled.
May be made night before serving.
Will keep for 2 to 3 days if put in a covered container.

title: tater candy
directions: Mix potato and powdered sugar.
Roll out on powdered sugar. Spread peanut butter on top.
Roll up and cut into pieces.
Let harden.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, sift dry ingredients and add to eggs. Add water and beat.
Add flavor and beat.
Put in 10 x 15-inch oiled pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Trim; cool.
Spread with jelly; roll.

title: micro-brittle
directions: Stir together nuts, sugar,
syrup
and	salt in a three quart bowl.
Place in microwave
oven and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after four
minutes.
Add butter and blend well. Return to oven and cook 2
to
minutes
or
until	nuts are golden brown. Add soda
and
vanilla
and
gently
stir until light and foamy. Pour onto greased cookie sheet and let cool. When cool break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: sugar free fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add chocolate and stir just until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in sweetener and vanilla.
Combine chocolate mixture with cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Stir in the nuts and spread mixture in a lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cherry mash candy
directions: Drain and cut cherries.
Mix all the above ingredients.
Chill in freezer 1 hour.
Make into walnut size balls.
Put in freezer and freeze overnight. Dip in chocolate.
Dip in bowl of finely chopped pecans.

title: lime waldorf salad
directions: In bowl, put 1/4 cup jello and 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in refrigerator.
In bowl, put balance of jello and 1 cup of boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water; put in refrigerator.

title: bacon-tomato spread
directions: Stir together the cream cheese, mustard and celery salt.
Fold in bacon, tomato and green pepper.
Pat into round ball.
Wrap in foil or clear plastic wrap.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix 1/2 to 3/4 can of chicken broth with one can of cream of chicken soup.
Add Veg-All and cooked chicken.
Put into pastry lined pie pan.
Top with other pie crust.
Crimp edges to seal; cut slits on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Yields 1 pie.

title: dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and white bread.
Pour soup, water and broth over bread and mix.
Add margarine, eggs, onion, sage, salt and pepper.
Mix together.
Taste and add extra salt and pepper if needed.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook about 45 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Add tomato and spaghetti sauce; simmer until thick.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: kielbasa cabbage soup
directions: Saute cabbage, onion and garlic in oil for 5 minutes or until tender.
Combine water, vinegar and brown sugar.
Add to cabbage. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 60 to 70 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: deviled crab
directions: Make smooth paste of flour and cream.
Heat smoothly and add butter.
Cook until very thick.
Add egg and other ingredients. Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: creamy swiss chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1 slice of Swiss cheese on each chicken breast.
Combine cream soup and liquid.
Pour over cheese.
Combine stuffing mix, seasoning and margarine.
Sprinkle over top of chicken.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve with Melinda's Seasoned Rice.

title: blueberry angel cake
directions: Cut cake into 3 equal layers (mark with toothpicks).
Mix the other ingredients together, icing layers with mixture.
Replace the layers.
Pour blueberry in center of cake and on top.

title: roast turkey breast
directions: Thaw turkey breast completely and place in the crock-pot. Season to taste with salt, pepper and sage.
Dot with butter. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: dijon potato salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add potatoes and mix.

title: chicken dressing and giblet gravy
directions: Crumble cornbread and white bread and add spices to mixture. Stir and smell and taste.
Add broth, if needed.
Saute the celery, onion and bell pepper in butter or broth.
In one 9 x 12-inch pan, place one-fourth of the chicken in bottom.
Pour 6 cups of dressing over and mix.
Makes 4 roasting pans (9 x 12-inch) full of dressing.
Can use one large roasting pan. Reserve 1 cup dressing mix for giblet gravy.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and margarine.
Add eggs, buttermilk and lemon flavoring.
Put ingredients in unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven about one hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend oleo, powder sugar, and cream cheese.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In pan, mix sugar, vinegar, ketchup, water, soy sauce and cornstarch mix.
Heat mixture over medium heat until thickened.

title: cheese cake
directions: Work margarine, flour and sugar until crumbly; press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool.

title: golden corn bread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth, about 1 minute. Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan or put in greased muffin pan cups. Bake at 425° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 4 minutes; drain and set aside.
In large bowl, combine soup, milk, onion, mustard and caraway seed.
Gently stir in chosen meat, drained sauerkraut and partially cooked noodles.
Put into greased 3-quart baking dish. Top with cheese.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs, melted butter and garlic powder.
Sprinkle over mixture in baking dish. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: lasagne(easy and good)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix meat and spaghetti sauce together.
Beat eggs; add cottage cheese, parsley, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in a small bowl.

title: liver and rice creole
directions: Cut liver into 1/2 inch cubes.
Coat with flour and saute in shortening until brown.
Add salt, tomato puree and peppers. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Alternate layers of rice and tomato mixture.
Combine cereal and margarine.
Sprinkle over liver. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated beef chunks
directions: Sprinkle roast with meat tenderizer.
Let stand for 1 hour. Cut roast into 2-inch chunks.
Place in a large bowl.
Add brown sugar, ginger, soy sauce, oil, garlic, pepper, m.s.g. and water. Mix well until meat is coated with marinade.
Marinate in refrigerator for 3 hours to overnight.
Grill beef chunks until done to taste.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix everything together.
Slice croissants 2/3 through.
Fill with chicken salad or serve on whole wheat or rye.
Excellent. Better after it sits a couple of hours, covered, in refrigerator. Yields 8 average croissants.

title: bean dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix all ingredients except cheese topping.
Place in two 8-inch pie pans.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 16 servings.

title: geneva's potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and dice them; cook, then cool.
Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
(Optional:
Add a little mustard.)
After salad is made, sprinkle about 3 teaspoons of sugar and mix.

title: southern living chicken salad
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; boil.
Debone and cut up.
Mix mayo and Cool Whip; mix with chicken.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
If dry, add more Cool Whip.
Great on croissants!

title: slush
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Serve frozen or slushy.
Will keep in freezer for a long time.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms and set aside.
Heat butter; add onion and saute until golden.
Add mushrooms, remaining vege tables and seasonings.
Cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Combine 1 tablespoon flour and 2 tablespoons cold water. Stir slowly into vegetable mixture.
Add boiling water and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Before serving, stir in milk or cream.
Add cheese.
Do not boil.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with tortillas.
Brown meat; drain. Layer in pan: meat, drained tomatoes, chili beans and soup.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix and add 1/2 cup chopped walnuts or pecans.
Put in dish and add nuts on top.
Has a `sweet n sour' taste.

title: pastry, never fail
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Divide dough into 5 equal parts.
Shape each into a ball and wrap tightly.
Chill.
May be stored up to 2 weeks in a refrigerator.
Yield: Pastry for 5 (9-inch) pies.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: In a bowl drain pineapple, reserving the juice in a saucepan. Mix together juice, 1/2 cup water and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring thoroughly. Break up cranberry sauce with fork and stir into gelatin mixture. Refrigerate until mixture begins to set.
Stir in pineapple and celery. Pour into a four-cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with 2 cups of crushed cornflakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted margarine. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook on medium heat the first 4 ingredients, until bubbling around the edges.
Remove from heat; stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn and bake at 200° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sesame street potatoes
directions: Place all ingredients, except sesame seed and paprika, in a large bowl.
Allow frozen potatoes to completely thaw.
Mix ingredients together.
Place in slightly greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle sesame seed and paprika over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower until fork-tender.
Place cream of mushroom soup in casserole dish.
Add 3/4 can milk; blend until smooth. Break up cauliflower into small pieces.
Place in soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Sprinkle Bisquick over everything.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until crust is golden brown.
Broccoli can be substituted.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend ingredients together in blender until thickened.

title: pita pizzas
directions: Spread pitas with ketchup.
Sprinkle on oregano.
Add sliced tomatoes, mushrooms, chopped onion, black olives and bell pepper. Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and bake for 10 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix cake, pudding mix and flour together.
Add remaining ingredients (excluding nuts) and beat 2 minutes.
Grease and flour Bundt pan; place nuts on bottom of pan.
Add batter.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Leave in pan.

title: suncoast scallops
directions: Pour 2 tablespoons of butter into a shallow baking pan; arrange scallops in single layer.
Combine breadcrumbs, garlic salt, mustard, paprika and remaining butter; sprinkle over scallops.
Broil 4 inches from heat until lightly browned, 6 to 8 minutes.
Drizzle sherry over scallops; serve hot with lemon wedges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: florentine salad(raw spinach salad in lime jelly.)
directions: Beat lime, water, vinegar, mayonnaise and salt with rotary beater.
Add cottage cheese.
Thaw and drain spinach well.
Let jello set a little before adding cheese, spinach and onion.
Makes a small salad.

title: creamy italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot. Combine salad dressing mix and water; pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 3 hours. In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and soup until blended. Pour over chicken. Cook 1 hour longer or until chicken juices run clear. Serve over rice or noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: grandma's wacky cake
directions: Mix together the flour, cocoa, baking soda, sugar and salt. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix and pour into cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together but the 7-Up.
Add it last and beat well.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for about 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar; add eggs.
Combine cocoa and food coloring to make a paste.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Sift flour and salt together.
Then with mixer at medium speed, add alternately with buttermilk to mixture.
Blend well and add vanilla.
Combine vinegar and baking
soda in small bowl; while foaming, add to batter.
Do not beat.
Stir gently.
Bake in two greased 8-inch pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: honey cookies
directions: Sift sugar and cream with shortening.
Add honey and salt. Beat in 1 at a time, the 2 eggs.
Sift flour.
Resift with baking powder and add this to the mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Make cookies small.

title: tutti-frutti cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add remainder of ingredients. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
